title: inedible cornstarch dough
directions: Combine ingredients over low heat and stir until consistency of stiff mashed potatoes. Remove from heat and cover with wet towel. Allow pan to cool enough to touch.
Remove mixture from pan and knead until smooth and dough-like.
On surface covered with wax paper, roll to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutters. Re-work excess, roll and cut.
Set ornaments on rack to air dry 4 to 5 hours.
Thin acrylic paint with water and paint; air dry. Paint, polyurethane or varnish; let dry. Ready to hang on tree, etc.
Makes 18 to 24 ornaments.

title: wine and cheese bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and the yeast.
In saucepan, combine wine, butter, salt and sugar.
Heat until warm and butter begins to melt (115° to 120°).
Remove from heat and stir until butter is melted.
Add to flour and yeast.
Add the 3 eggs and beat 1/2 minute to mix, using spatula and electric mixer. Beat 3 minutes at high speed, scraping sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
By hand, stir in shredded cheese and enough of the flour to make a soft dough that can be handled.

title: broccoli puffs
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions (omit salt).
Drain and place in a 10 x 16-inch pan.
Stir soup and cheese; gradually add mayonnaise, milk and beaten egg.
Pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw bread about 3 hours (don't let rise).
Roll one loaf to rectangle (about 16 x 15-inch or smaller).
Brush with oil.
(Leave 1-inch margarine around dough.) Cover with pepperoni slices, then cover that with cheese.
Then cover with pepper rings (well drained).
Roll up like jelly roll and bake about 45 minutes on cookie sheet (2 on each sheet). Brush with oil every 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
In a medium casserole dish, layer 1/3 cooked elbow spaghetti and 1/3 of cheese slices.
Repeat the layers 2 more times.
Dot butter on top and add milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is brown.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken for 10 minutes in 3 quarts of water.
Remove chicken to cool.
Cook rice in chicken stock.
Cut chicken into small chunks.
Stir together sour cream, soup and spices.
Place half of drained rice in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle onion and spread soup mixture on top of rice.
Layer remaining rice, grated cheese, Ro-Tel and tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham salad
directions: Cut up ham; add green onions, celery, tomatoes and bell pepper.
Cook
macaroni;
drain
and
add to ham mixture.
Add salad
dressing to taste and preferred consistency.
Refrigerate for about 2 hours before serving.

title: hydrox dessert
directions: Cook marshmallows, milk and beaten egg yolks until marshmallows dissolve.
Cool.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Mix all ingredients together, except candy bars.
Crush chilled candy bars and add to mixture.
Crush cookies fine.
Put 1/2 of crumbs in an 8 x 11-inch dish.
Pour pudding mixture over the crumbs and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: spareribs with sauerkraut
directions: Season ribs with salt and pepper.
Place in Dutch oven. Combine kraut (including liquid) with remaining ingredients and spoon over ribs.
Bake, covered, in moderate oven (350°) for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours or until ribs are done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: raisin bread
directions: Combine milk, sugar, margarine and salt.
Cool to room temperature.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to the milk mixture.
Beat in egg and then 2 cups flour.
Add raisins and mix with a spoon.
Stir in the remaining flour until mix is stiff (elastic).
Place in bowl for 2 hours to rise with the greased side up.
Roll out and cover side with cinnamon and sugar; roll up to fit bread pan.
Let rise for 1/2 hour and cook at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: deviled ham cheese ball
directions: Cream together Philadelphia cream cheese, celery and garlic salt, parsley flakes and deviled ham.
Stir in Cheddar cheese.
Set in refrigerator until almost hard.
Shape into ball or use mold. If mold is used, grease pan and line with pecans.
Spoon mixture in, then refrigerate until firm.
If shaped into ball, roll the ball into chopped nuts.

title: layered tuna salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, green onions and mustard.
Set aside. Toss tuna with dill.
In a 3-quart serving bowl layer lettuce, shells, cucumber, tomato, tuna, peas and bacon (in that order). Spread salad dressing mixture over bacon, sealing to edge of bowl. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover.
Chill several hours or overnight. Toss to serve.

title: peach cobbler no. 2
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Peel peaches and slice.
Toss peaches with 1 cup of the sugar, lemon juice, nutmeg and 3 tablespoons of the flour.
Put in baking dish.

title: whipped carrots and potatoes
directions: Place potato, carrots and onion in pan; boil until very tender.
Drain.
Mash vegetables together in bowl.
Add milk, margarine, tarragon and pepper; beat until smooth.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Lightly brown hamburger and onion in frying pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When browned, add soup and paprika.
Put a layer of potatoes on bottom of buttered casserole; cover with layer of meat mixture, then another layer of potatoes.
Pour enough milk over all until it shows around the edges.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: white chip chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in white chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake; cookies will be soft.
They will puff while baking; flatten upon cooling.) Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Yield 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion; drain fat.
Add all contents of the cans; mix together.
Add seasoning.
Stir and cook until hot.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Spread 1/3 cup sour cream in bottom of baking dish.
Use 2 cups of sour cream and mix all ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
In a skillet, heat 1 tortilla at a time in a small amount of oil.
Put 1/4 cup chicken mixture in each tortilla and roll up.
Spread top with sour cream and grated cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peach or fruit cobbler or pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, oleo, salt and milk.
Add peaches; mix well. Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: creamy corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: my favorite cobbler
directions: Mix together milk, flour and sugar.
Pour melted margarine into baking dish, then pour flour mixture in baking dish on top of margarine.
Next, pour fruit into center of flour mixture. Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in uncovered 1-quart casserole for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: goofy bars
directions: Pour dry cake mix into bowl.
Put eggs into measuring cup; add enough water to make 2/3 cup.
Add this to the cake mix, along with the brown sugar.
Beat until blended.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and marshmallows over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: no stir fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole.
Meanwhile, stir together the flour, sugar and milk.
Pour this batter over melted butter.
Do not stir!
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: polenta pie
directions: Prepare polenta according to package directions and in the amount desired.
Butter a baking dish of appropriate size and spread a layer of polenta on the bottom.
Pour some tomato sauce; sprinkle with cubed Mozzarella and any other meat or vegetable you are using.
Add remaining polenta; sprinkle with sauce, grated Parmesan cheese, rosemary and olive oil.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly, about 45 minutes.
Let rest; cut and serve.

title: brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie plate.
Melt margarine over very low heat.
Stir in chocolate.
Beat in sugar and eggs well.
Add flour gradually, beating just until combined. Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into pie plate and bake for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: brownies
directions: Melt
chocolate
and
oleo
in	saucepan
or microwave. Allow to	cool
to
lukewarm.
Add sugar and eggs; blend well. Add flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 2 x 8 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.	Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May
be
frosted,
if desired.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen.

title: bbq sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Lower heat and boil gently 15 minutes, until thickened.

title: autumn butternut casserole
directions: Season squash with 1/4 cup butter, 1 tablespoon brown sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper. Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons butter in a skillet; add sliced apples. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar. Cover and simmer over low heat until barely tender (about 5 minutes). Spread in a 3-quart casserole; spoon mashed squash evenly over apples. Mix cornflakes with pecans, 1/2 cup brown sugar and melted butter. Sprinkle over squash. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread rolls on large cookie sheet and bake as directed.
Mix cream cheese, garlic powder, dill weed and mayo.
Mix until creamy and spread over cooled dough; add vegetables and sprinkle over all of the dough.
Cover with wax paper and set in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Press wax paper down lightly to hold down vegetables.
Cut in 2-inch squares and serve.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Heat milk.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool. Drain blueberries.
Beat cream.
Add the milk-marshmallow mixture. Then add the blueberries, no juice.
Chill.
Use graham cracker or cookie crumbs for top and bottom.
Chill and serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and drop by teaspoon, one at a time.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen cookies.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Freeze.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sour cream and almond extract; mix.
Add flour, soda and powder.
Beat well.
Put one tablespoon batter in each muffin cup.
Add 1 teaspoon jam and 1/2 to 1 teaspoon almond paste.
Fill with more batter and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until golden.
Makes 12 to 14 muffins.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine with jello in bowl on lettuce.
Serve with salad dressing.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put hamburger in pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup.
Spread with mushroom soup.
Top with Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until done, 1 hour, in oven at 350°.

title: ice cream
directions: All golden, pure and sweet,

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles in 3 quarts of salted water.
Brown ground meat in 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green pepper and onions.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine the crumbs, 2 tablespoons cheese, oregano, garlic and pepper.
Roll the chicken in this mixture. Arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, turn and bake for another 20 minutes. Blend the soup and the milk.
Pour over the chicken. Sprinkle with the paprika and the remaining cheese. Bake another 20 minutes.

title: coney island hot dogs
directions: Brown beef slowly, but thoroughly, breaking it up with a fork until crumbly.
Drain off fat.
Return to pan and stir in water, onion, garlic, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer until thick, about 20 minutes.
Serve over heated hot dogs in toasted split hot dog buns.
Garnish with chopped onion, if desired.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the pumpkin and milk together.
Add the beaten egg yolks. Add the sugar which has been mixed with the cinnamon, cloves, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well and fold in the egg whites. Pour pumpkin mixture in pie crust.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 375° and bake for 30 minutes longer or until filling is firm.
(Bake in a 9-inch Pyrex pan.)

title: pumpkin muffins(no oil and no sugar.)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine and mix remaining ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to wet and stir thoroughly.
(Do not beat.)
Bake in nonstick muffin tin for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a large baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pear pie
directions: Combine pears, lemon juice, 1 teaspoon lemon peel, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Place in unbaked pie shell. Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top of pear mixture. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put on low fire and stir until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook fast 3 minutes.
Remove top and cook to hard ball stage when dropped into water.
Add vanilla and pour over popcorn.
Use hands to shape balls.

title: orange cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water.
Mix well. While cake is hot, punch holes in cake.
Pour mixture over cake slowly.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend all ingredients.
Pour 3/4 of mix into a greased tube pan.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon over cake batter.
Pour remaining mix in pan over sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar and milk mix.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Take a Bundt Cake pan.
Cut each biscuit in half.
Dip each piece of biscuit into melted butter, then cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Put into Bundt cake pan, stacking them on top of one another.

title: boo's san antonio chili
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, brown beef *(have substituted deer, ground up) and pour off fat. Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Cook and stir until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Cover; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour. Serve with corn chips and shredded Cheddar cheese if desired. Makes about 4 quarts.

title: frothy milk punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl, beat until frothy with whisk or electric mixer.
Pour into chilled punch bowl and serve with ice ring made of pineapple and orange juice decorated with fresh whole strawberries and mint leaves.

title: yellow lemon cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until set.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water; let set for awhile.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well altogether.
Put into an oblong pan to set, then serve.
Can be made ahead of time.
Keeps well in fridge.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Have pan with hot grease ready.
Put 1/2 full of batter and then sprinkle cheese on top.
Fill with rest of batter to top of pan.
Cook at 500° until brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook hamburg and add remaining ingredients.
Add enough water to get the right consistency.
Bring to a boil.

title: sweet and sour pork over rice
directions: Combine flour, egg, salt and water to make thin batter.
Add pork cubes to batter mix until well coated.
Fry in hot cooking oil until browned.
Drain.
Combine green pepper strips, pineapple, brown sugar, vinegar, 1 cup water and molasses.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes, cut in eighths. Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Add to hot mixture.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Add pork and cook 5 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in bowl.
Microwave 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and salt.
Microwave 9 to 12 minutes on High or until threads.
Immediately stir in butter and soda. Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Cool, lifting often to keep from sticking.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Dissolve sugar, salt and margarine in hot milk.
Cool milk lukewarm.
Add yeast and beaten eggs.
Stir in flour and beat until smooth.
Let rise 45 minutes. Roll out and cut round shapes.
Put a small dab of margarine and fold.
Let rise another 45 minutes.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Prepare pudding mixes in separate bowls and add 1/2 container Cool Whip to each bowl of pudding.
Line a 9 x 13-inch container with graham crackers.
Spread one batch of pudding and Cool Whip over graham crackers.
Make another layer of graham crackers and add second bowl of pudding and Cool Whip.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Bring next 3 ingredients to a boil and boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Cool. Pour over top of crackers.
Cover and refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: aunt ruth's rhubarb goodie
directions: Layer half of each ingredient, except water, in a 9 x 13-inch pan and repeat.
Add water and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together.
When completely melted, add peanut butter and mix well.
Put marshmallows and peanuts together in a large bowl.
Pour chip mixture over the marshmallows and peanuts; mix well.
Pat into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: james' crab cakes
directions: Beat egg until lemon colored.
Fold in all the ingredients. Mix well.
Gradually add pieces of crabmeat until mixture has a good texture.
Form medium size crab cakes.
(Serving for 8.) Place in large frypan (use butter) on medium heat.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Cool on sheet of wax paper.

title: tutti-frutti roll
directions: Blend all ingredients and shape into roll.
You may roll the roll in coconut.
Keep
in refrigerator wrapped in Saran Wrap.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and mix well. Add flour, salt, soda and bananas.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for one hour.

title: bobbi's corn chowder
directions: Cut bacon in 1/2-inch pieces and fry until crisp.
Remove and save 2 to 3 tablespoons bacon grease. Add onion and celery. Cook until tender.
Blend in flour and bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add milk and stir well.
Add other ingredients and cook until tender.

title: chicken 'n rice delight
directions: Boil chicken in water with salt and pepper until it comes off the bones.
Debone chicken; return to broth.
Add garbanzo beans. Bring to a boil and add rice and cardamon.
Cook until rice is done and water is gone.
Brown sunflower seeds in margarine and set aside.
Serve chicken and rice on platter topped with yogurt and sprinkled with sunflower seeds.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix ground chuck, soup mix, egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper until well blended.
Form into loaf and place in oblong casserole.
Cover top of meat loaf with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.
(This meat loaf does not make a gravy.)

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour until blended.
Stir in cream slowly.
When the sauce is thick, stir in catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Add shrimp and crabmeat.
Stir about until well heated. Season with salt, paprika and cayenne.
Just before serving, add sherry.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: no bake easy cheesecake
directions: Follow directions on the back of Jell-O cheesecake mix for graham cracker crumbs (or you can use ladyfingers instead).
Put graham cracker crumbs in the spring-pan lined on the bottom as well as the sides.
Put graham crackers in the refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together; beat together for 10 minutes.
Pour beaten mixture into spring pan with the graham crackers; then refrigerate for 4 hours.
Top with favorite toppings and enjoy.

title: hot reuben dip
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix cream cheese, 1 c. of the Swiss cheese, the dressing and corned beef. Spread in pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4 inches, or quiche dish, 9 x 1 1/2 inches. Top with sauerkraut and remaining 1/2 c. Swiss cheese. Bake about 15 minutes or until bubbly around the edge. Serve hot with pretzel crackers or cocktail rye bread. This has 2 gm carbohydrates.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Add butter, mixing well.
Spoon into 9-inch square baking pan.
Press into pan evenly.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: *Brown first and set aside.

title: fancy fast chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top each piece with a slice of cheese.
Arrange sliced mushrooms over the cheese.
Mix soup and wine; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over top; drizzle melted butter on.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
(If boneless chicken breasts, bake for about 45 minutes.)

title: fast crustless quiche
directions: Butter a 10-inch pie plate or a regular-size quiche pan.
In it sprinkle the first 3 ingredients.
In blender, put last 7 ingredients.
Blend it all for one minute.
Pour over the ingredients in the pie plate and bake for 35 minutes at 350°, if you use a metal pie plate.
If you use a glass pie plate, cook a little bit longer.
Let stand three or four minutes before serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Pour liquid over vegetables.
Press down.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Combine shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni soup
directions: Peel a couple of potatoes and cut into small pieces.
Place in water to cook, then peel an onion and dice up into the potatoes. If you want to, add a little garlic.
Boil the potatoes, onion and a little garlic until done.
Drain the water from the potatoes and save the water.
Mash the potatoes and pour into the water mixture.
If you want, add a little more if the water mixture is too strong.
Then make thickening (a little flour and milk mixed together), then add the thickening to the water mixture and boil. Place the soup in a bowl with a little crackers.
Put yourself in chair and stuff your mouth.
Just for fun!

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Grease pie plate.
Mix drained shrimp, shredded cheese, cream cheese (cut in cubes) and minced onion onto pie plate.
Blend eggs, milk, Bisquick and salt in blender for 15 seconds.
Pour over shrimp.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed grapes with lemon cream
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar, lemon peel and lemon juice until smooth.

Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. With a sharp knife, cut an X through the top of each grape, being careful not to cut all the way through the bottom. Spread sections apart slightly. Spoon filling into a pastry bag fitted with a 1/2-inch star tip.
Pipe the filling into each grape. Grapes may be prepared and refrigerated up to 4 hours before serving.
Yields approximately 3 1/2 dozen grapes.

title: watergate
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Pour pudding into large bowl. Stir in Cool Whip and pineapple.
Chill and serve.

title: coconut buckeyes
directions: Blend sugar and margarine.
Add coconut, milk and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls a little smaller than 1 inch. Refrigerate to make solid.

title: green beans with hazelnut-lemon butter
directions: In a saucepan, cover beans with water.
Cover and cook until crisp-tender, about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a small saucepan over medium heat, brown the butter.
Add the hazelnuts, lemon juice, parsley, basil and salt; heat through.
Drain beans.
Add the butter mixture and toss to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown
ground beef.
Add garlic, onion, sausages, salt, pepper, barbecue
sauce
and relish.
Cook over low heat about 15 minutes.
Serve over hot buns.

title: quick and easy pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and oil.
Stir in flour gradually, enough to make a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise on greased cookie sheet while preparing toppings.
Shape pizza dough with hands; let rise to 1/2 of finished thickness.
Spread on desired toppings.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes (low rack in oven).

title: cinnamon drops
directions: Mix Bisquick, water and 1/2 of the sugar.
Roll balls of dough into remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Coat entire surface.
Bake on greased sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pasta surprise
directions: Remove sausages from casing. Brown in skillet. Add onion, mushrooms and snow peas. Drain well. Add apple at the very end or it will overcook.
Boil pasta.
Drain, then add the meat and vegetable mix.
Toss the cheese throughout the pasta.
Cover and let stand for a few minutes until cheese melts.
Chicken can be used in place of the sausages.
Garlic and other vegetables can also be added.

title: waffles
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon color. Beat in milk. Stir or fold in dry ingredients. Add melted margarine and fold or stir. Pour into hot waffle iron. Makes several waffles.

title: prune cake
directions: Cut prunes into small pieces and pour boiling water over them. Let stand a few minutes and drain off water.
Mix oil and sugar; add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk. Add prunes and nuts.
Bake in a greased tube pan or in baking pans at 350° until done (about 45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook onions and zucchini in salted water; drain.
Combine soup, carrots, sour cream and fold into zucchini and onion.
Mix melted butter and stuffing.
Spread half of this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan (greased).
Spread zucchini mixture over this, then spread rest of stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Beat
eggs
very
well and set aside. Cream the butter, shortening	and sugar until light and fluffy. Add beaten eggs. Sift together flour, baking
powder
and
salt. Add to creamed mixture and alternate with	milk. Stir in flavorings. Spoon in floured and greased tube pan.
Bake
for
1 1/2 hours at 325°. Cool in pan for 8 minutes before turning out.

title: duck and rice
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and fry until lightly brown.
Then add beef bouillon.
Cook rice and stir into first mixture.
Split the ducks in half; dust in flour, salt and pepper and quick-fry in butter until light brown.
Put rice mixture in large casserole or roasting pan and place the duck on top of rice.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: artichoke cheese squares
directions: Saute onion and garlic in small amount of liquid from artichoke can.
Chop artichoke in bowl.
Add eggs, seasonings, onion, garlic, bread crumbs and cheese.
Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Salt and pepper inside dressed poultry.
Then boil in enough water to cover and cook until tender.
Be sure to have at least 3 cups of water remaining after poultry has cooked.
If less than this remains, add enough hot water to make up the difference.
Add 1/4 cup butter.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecued pork burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and form into 1/4 pound patties.
Sear on grill, then reduce flame and cook over direct heat, about 10 minutes each side.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Cut cheese into thin strips; place in bag.
Add flour, toss. Toss well until cheese is coated.
Split garlic clove in half; rub inside of fondue pot well with cut sides of both halves.
Press 1/4 clove garlic; place in fondue pot.
Add Sauterne, place over flame. Heat until bubbles start to rise, do not cover or boil.
Add cheese gradually; cook over low flame, stirring constantly, until melted. Stir in pepper and nutmeg; add warmed Sauterne if mixture becomes too thick.
Serve with French bread cubes, cauliflower flowerets, mushrooms and rolled pepperoni slices for dipping.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until tender.
Remove skin from chicken.
Pull chicken into small pieces and place in bottom of 12 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix in medium size bowl, cornbread, loaf bread, eggs, sage, black pepper and celery or celery seed. Mix and pour over chicken and bake in 400° oven until brown, about 1 hour.

title: brisket with mustard sauce
directions: Boil any size brisket in large heavy kettle with chopped onion and bay leaf.
After 3 to 4 hours, remove to roasting pan.
Scrape off and remove all fat.
Spread with sauce: prepared mustard, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread over all sides of brisket.
Place in 450° oven and bake 15 minutes, just before serving.
Slice and serve.

title: hot cider
directions: Boil cider, brown sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon sticks and cloves. Strain and add orange juice and lemon juice.

title: brown rice and chicken
directions: Blend and heat chicken soup and water.
Put rice in bottom of casserole, pour over rice, 1/3 of soup mixture and sprinkle 1/3 onion soup.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt, seasoned salt to taste. Lay chicken parts on top of rice, cover with remaining soup mixture and sprinkle with remaining dry soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Add liquid, wine or water, if it looks dry cooking.
Serves 6. This will freeze nicely.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix margarine and stuffing.
Sprinkle half in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Distribute small pieces of chicken over this.
Mix the 2 soups with broth and pour over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, removing foil for the last 10 minutes.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes, cut in halves, scoop out of shell and mash. Mix mashed potatoes together with the remaining ingredients. Spoon back into shells.
Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and combine the juice, egg, sugar, flour, and vinegar in small saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Cool completely.
Fold in whipped topping and 1/2 c peanuts.
Peel, core, and slice apples.
Fold apples and pineapple into cooled mixture.
Garnish with remaining peanuts.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Stir yeast into water until dissolved.
Mix in flour.
Let sit for 2 to 3 days in 2-quart dish with cover at room temperature.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into quarters.
Put layer of potatoes in ovenproof (9 x 13-inch) dish.
Arrange peppers, cut lengthwise, into about 8 strips around and over potatoes.
Place onions, cut in quarters, among potatoes and peppers.
Pour Italian dressing over vegetables.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pastry chef tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine pie crust mix with egg. Add just enough water to form dough.
Form 2 to 3 tablespoons dough into a round.
Press each round onto bottom and sides 3 to 4-inch tart pan.
(Use tart pans with removable bottoms, if possible.) Pierce pastry several times with a fork.
Place on a baking sheet. Bake for 10 minutes or until golden; cool slightly.
Remove tart shells from pans; cool completely on racks.
Pour half and half into a small bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon into tart shells.
Chill until ready to serve.
Arrange fruit on pudding.
Garnish with mint leaves, if desired.

title: chicken crunch casserole
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients. Stir soup into mayonnaise. Toss chicken mixture. Turn into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with noodles. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until mixture is bubbly.

title: sweet white bread
directions: Melt yeast, milk and margarine, then mix all ingredients. When mixed, sprinkle flour on board and knead dough.
Separate into 2 loaves.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all well.
Put into greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: egg-filled rolls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Cut rolls in half.
Dig out the inside to make a hole in each half.
Put some filling in bottom half.
Place the top half on and wrap in foil.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Bake 15 to 29 minutes at 350°.

title: brown bread
directions: Moisten All-Bran and raisins in milk.
Add sugar and molasses. Add flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Bake in 4 (1-pound) size cans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fannie's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: pineapple pepper cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, pineapple, onion, peppers, 1/2 cup of pecans and other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator to firm; then roll into ball, covering with remaining pecans.
Place a cherry in center of ball for color.
Serve with fancy crackers.

title: flaky baking powder biscuits
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add egg and milk; mix.
Turn out on floured surface and knead lightly 15 times.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Put in pineapple.
Add 1 1/2 cups of sugar; stir well.
Prepare jello with 4 cups of boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add to fruit and sprinkle with nuts. Keeps well in refrigerator or freezer.

title: microwave mexican casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap; fold back to allow steam to escape. Microwave at High 6 to 7 minutes, until meat is browned, stirring once.
Drain.
Add mushroom soup, enchilada sauce and milk; stir well.
Place 2 cups tortilla chips in 2-quart shallow casserole. Spoon half of ground beef mixture over chips; layer with chiles and half of cheese.
Top with remaining ground beef mixture.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; turn back edge to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 10 to 12 minutes, turning dish after 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; let stand 5 minutes. Garnish with remaining chips and peppers.
Serve with shredded lettuce and tomato.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Add onion, green pepper and celery; set aside.

title: baked cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Grease 9x13 inch pan.
Brown ground beef in skillet, drain.
Stir in pizza sauce and mushrooms.
Unroll dough, press in greased pan.
Spoon hamburger mixture over crust. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown. 8 servings.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add pineapple to sugar.
Bring to boiling point and add gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Add lemon and cherry juice.
Cool.
Mash cream cheese and chopped cherries.
Combine with pineapple mixture adding a small amount at a time.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip cream and blend with salad mixture.
Mold and chill.

title: turkey hash
directions: Mix 1/2 can of Chinese noodles with the diced turkey.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash sweet potatoes and dry well. Grease the outside of potatoes with oil.
Price the skins with a fork.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Split open each potato and add butter.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix ahead 1 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon vinegar.
Beat together until very light the shortening, cocoa, sugar, salt, vanilla, eggs and food coloring.
Add flour alternately with the buttermilk.
Fold soda and vinegar mixture into the batter.
Pour into three greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cook milk mixed gradually with 4 tablespoons flour and let cool.
Mix sugar, shortening and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Add cooled mixture, one teaspoon at a time, beating into sugar and shortening.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar.
Spread between top of layers.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix tea, fruit juices,	red candies and sugar to taste. Heat to serving	temperature.
Add
ginger ale.	Yield:	about 25 cups.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In large bowl combine first 5 ingredients; cut in margarine until it looks like coarse meal.
Stir in raisins.
Combine buttermilk, 1 egg and baking soda; stir into flour mixture just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Knead on floured board until smooth.
Shape into ball and place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
With sharp knife cut a 4-inch cross about 1/2 inch deep in center of dough.
(Makes a decorative top.)
Brush with beaten egg yolk.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) about 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack before cutting.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and mayonnaise.
Boil slowly over low heat until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill until firm, stirring occasionally so ingredients are mixed well.
This takes several hours to set.

title: julia's curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit and arrange in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Melt butter, sugar and curry together in microwave.
Spoon over fruit. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Fill a roasting pan with popped corn.
In another pan, combine sugar, oleo, syrup and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt and baking soda.
Blend and pour over popcorn.
Mix well and place in 250° oven for 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally from bottom.
Spread on sheet of waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Blend cake mix, one egg and margarine with a mixer.
Mixture will be stiff.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, 10x sugar, 2 eggs, flavoring and salt until smooth. Pour over first mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Best if sets overnight.
Enjoy.

title: hamburger bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and add all remaining ingredients to this. Combine in baking dish.
Heat until bubbly.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: Spray a 9-inch pie plate with nonstick spray coating.
In medium mixing bowl, stir together chicken or turkey, corn and green chili peppers.
Spread mixture in pie plate.
In the same bowl, stir together eggs and milk.
Beat in flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken mixture.

title: cristell's microwave fish
directions: Mix batter as directed.
Dip fish pieces in batter.
Place fish pieces in microwave baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste. Put bits of butter and lemon juice over fish.
Next, place green pepper and onion on top of fish.
Bake in microwave oven for 9 minutes on High temperature or until done.
Do not turn fish.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Cut in small cubes the cheese, onions, pickles (or relish), apples and eggs.

Leave a small portion of the pickle, cheese and egg to garnish top of salad. Mix all ingredients together and when thoroughly mixed, grate some cheese, cut strips of pickle and strips of eggs to put on top. Serves about 9 small servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until soft.
Mix noodles, soup and tuna together. Add peas.
Pour mixture into dish and top with mashed potato chips.
Brown in a 350° oven.

title: crock pot beans
directions: Cook beans 1 hour on high in just enough water to cover 2 inches above beans.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on high for 4 hours.
Turn on low and cook for 10 hours.

title: quick icing
directions: Beat vanilla pudding and milk on low 2 minutes; set aside. Mix sugar, vanilla and Crisco well.
Add both mixtures together and beat until fine.

title: baked beans
directions: Corn may
be cooked right in the husk in your microwave oven. Place on a paper towel and turn ears over and rearrange after one-half of cooking time.

title: heavenly pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and mix well.
Add melted margarine, nutmeg and lemon extract.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
A blender may be used. Pour into freezer can and finish filling with milk to about 3 inches from top.
Makes 1 gallon to 5 quarts.

title: pop corn balls
directions: Boil ingredients until the mixture spins long threads when poured into ice water. Add 3/4 tsp. vanilla. Pour over three quarts of popcorn. Carefully form into balls.
Especially neat when covered in different colors of transparent tissue. Teens enjoyed doing this recipe for fund raisers. It can be multiplied for quantity.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a bowl.
Arrange chicken in pan. Pour mixture over entire chicken pieces and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered. Serve with rice, if desired.

title: beef and potato bake
directions: In a 3-quart baking dish, combine potatoes, oil and pepper. Firmly press into dish. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: miracle custard pie
directions: In blender, combine milk, eggs, flour, butter, vanilla and salt.
Cover.
Blend about 10 seconds or until mixed (do not overblend).
Stir in coconut. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken and wild rice soup
directions: Cook the chicken breasts, potatoes and carrots together; drain well.
Combine all above; simmer slowly.

title: salmon canapes
directions: In a small bowl, mix salmon, celery and minced green onion. Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, pepper and liquid smoke.
Mix well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour to develop flavor or up to 24 hours.
Just before serving, place a cucumber slice on crackers or toast.
Top with salmon mixture and garnish with green onion slices and watercress.
Makes 1 cup.

title: no cook peanut clusters
directions: Do not cook!
Combine and melt altogether on low heat until everything blends together well.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered cookie sheet.

title: pineapple fluff pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add softened cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Add drained pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts and chill.
Yield:
2 pies.

title: willard's famous barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients. Heat some to aid in blending flavors. Let cool and then bottle and cap sauce.
Does not need refrigerating.
Yields approximately 2 1/2 gallons.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, cocoa and sugar.
In bowl, combine eggs, vanilla, flour and pecans.
Combine 2 mixtures and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain off juice from pickles and put pickles in a big bowl. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and put in refrigerator.

title: aunt lil's brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla and melted margarine.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder and add to egg mixture, mixing well.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: sumptuous grilled shrimp and scallops
directions: Combine dressing, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Place shrimp, scallops and onion in a large container.
Cover with marinade and refrigerate overnight.
Thread shrimp, scallops and onion onto skewers.
Cover grill with foil punched with holes.
Place over coals.
Place skewers on foil. Cook with cover on grill until shrimp and scallops are cooked thoroughly (25 minutes).
Turn occasionally, brushing with marinade.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Saute ground beef in oil until red color disappears. Stir in seasoned salt.
In a saucepan, mix Spanish rice mix, tomato sauce and water. Simmer 5 minutes.
Line the bottom and sides of an oiled 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch casserole with 4 to 5 tortillas, dipping each first in sauce.
If necessary, cut to fit. Top with layers of 1/2 of the ground beef, 1/2 of the onions and 1 can sliced olives. Sprinkle with 1 cup of the cheese.

Dip 2 tortillas in sauce; lay on top of mixture. Repeat layers. Pour all but 1/2 cup of sauce over all. Dip remaining tortillas in sauce and arrange on top. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese. Cover with foil. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Remove foil the last 5 minutes of cooking. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Parboil vegetables.
Combine Cheez Whiz and soups by heating and blending.
One half hour before serving, mix everything together with 1/2 can onion rings.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes.
Top with balance of onion rings and bake another 5 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix next 4 ingredients (sugar, salt, shortening and water) with electric mixer.
Cool.
Add eggs and beat.
Add dissolved yeast and 4 cups of flour.
Beat with mixer.
Add and hand mix remaining flour.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and divide into rolls.

title: tod's bubble blintz ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut cream cheese into 20 pieces.
Roll each piece to about 3 inches in diameter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon. Place one cheese ball and 1 teaspoon cinnamon/sugar mix onto biscuit.
Pinch dough to seal.
Pour 1/2 melted butter into bottom of 5-cup ring mold.
Sprinkle 1/2 nuts and 1/2 remaining cinnamon/sugar mix into the mold.
Place ten of the rolls atop mixture, seam side up; pour 1/4 butter/nuts/cinnamon/sugar on this layer; repeat layering and finish pouring remaining mixes on top. Bake for 20 minutes until browned.
Cool 5 minutes; invert onto serving plate.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Mix soup, milk, horseradish and mustard until warm.
Combine vegetables and cheese.
Add sauce.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon in medium bowl and mix well.
In another bowl, combine coconut, pecans, dates and apples. Sprinkle 1/4 cup flour mixture over fruit mixture and mix.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla and mix well. Add flour mixture and fruit mix.
(You will need heavy-duty mixer or blend by hand.)
Bake in greased pan (tube or sheet) at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: best-ever cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and white sugar thoroughly. Beat in eggs and flavoring.
Add oatmeal and let stand awhile. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in fruit, nuts or chocolate chips, if desired.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 8 1/2 dozen.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice.
Combine fruit and pecans in a large bowl and toss gently.
Combine pudding mix and reserved pineapple juice in a mixing bowl.
Beat on high speed of electric mixer 1 minute.
Pour pudding mixture over fruit and pecans.
Toss gently.
Refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peanut chews
directions: Pour honey and maple syrup into saucepan and cook until a small amount of mixture forms a hard ball when dropped into very cold water (255° F on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat, add soda and cream of tartar; mix well.
Stir in nuts and pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2 inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes sixty-four 1 inch squares.

title: grandma's chocolate layer cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch round layer pans. Sift together into mixing bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add shortening, 2/3 cup milk and vanilla. Beat vigorously for 2 minutes (300 strokes). You can use electric mixer if you scrape the sides down often. Use medium speed. Add another 1/3 cup milk and 2 eggs. Beat
2 minutes. Pour into prepared pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool. Finish with Whiz Chocolate Fudge Flavor Frosting.

title: lavender potpourri
directions: Mix together in a glass container, tightly covered, for 2 to 4 weeks.
Shake the container daily.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and place in baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Melt butter.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, onion, almonds, sherry, basil and rosemary.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve over hot rice.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes and gradually add sugar and pumpkin. Combine flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread into a greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Top with the chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Turn out on a terrycloth towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll cake and towel up together.
Cool, then unroll and spread filling on. Reroll and chill.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Beat 1 egg until frothy and 1 tablespoon water.
Melt butter in pan; stir a lot.
Add sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Put pecans in egg white and coat well, then put them into sugar and spices; cover well.
Place in pan with butter and bake at 250° until done.

title: cinnamon swirl rounds
directions: Will need three 8 x 1 1/2-inch greased cake pans.

title: cream puff filling
directions: Make dream whip according to package.
Make pudding with remaining 2 Cups milk.
Fold dream whip into pudding.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls onto pan.
Bake at temperature indicated on can for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Mix well the cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on top of the baked rolls. Add shredded vegetables, press slightly.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: easy brownies
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing
bowl
and
beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Bake in greased and
floured 10 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Keep well covered.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Place yeast in warm water and stir with fork until dissolved. Set aside.
Melt margarine and cream with sugar and egg.
Add to yeast mixture.
Add flour, stirring well.
Place in airtight container for 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: fruit tart
directions: Crust:
Combine flours and 1 tablespoon sugar; cut in margarine until dough resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle with ice water and toss until crumbly; form into a ball.
Put ball of dough between two pieces of wax paper and roll into a 10-inch circle.
Remove top sheet of wax paper and invert onto an ungreased baking sheet. Remove remaining wax paper and crimp pastry edges.
Prick all over with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes (should be lightly browned).
Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Do not beat.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in two greased loaf pans at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix everything together with enough mayonnaise to make a "thicken" mixture.
Serve with chunks of French bread.

title: joan's strawberry jello
directions: Crust:
Mix pretzels, melted margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: barley casserole
directions: Lightly brown barley and onion in oil and butter. Combine broth, mushrooms and juice in casserole.
Add barley and onions. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Uncover.
Put slivered almonds on top and bake 5 or 6 minutes longer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown meats and onion together; drain off fat.
Cook (boil) potatoes; mash them.
Heat chopped broccoli.
Pour meat in bottom of deep casserole dish.
Next, sprinkle seasonings over top. Spoon over mushroom soup and spread evenly over meat.
Place a layer of cooked broccoli on top of soup.
Sprinkle half of each package of cheese.
Spoon on mashed potatoes evenly.
Sprinkle on Parmesan and remaining Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 375° until top is browned and cheese melted.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Roll 8 beans in 1/2 slice of bacon. Secure with toothpick. There will be enough rolls to fill an 11 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt oleo, add sugar, then eggs; beat well.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Then add flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cut in squares while warm.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt in medium bowl, reserving 1/2 cup sugar.
Heat water to boiling in medium size pan.
Lower heat.
Add sugar mixture, stirring constantly for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks slightly in small bowl.
Stir in 1/2 cup of sugar mixture.
Stir back into mixture in pan and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Stir in lemon rind, juice and butter.
Beat egg whites and lemon extract.
Add reserved sugar, one tablespoon at a time until it stands in peaks. Put filling in crust.
Put egg white mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: easy chocolate snack cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in bowl with fork.
Stir in water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into ungreased pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar if desired.
Also good with chocolate chips sprinkled over hot cake.

title: strawberry crumble cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cook the sugar, water and cornstarch until thickens; remove from heat.
Add the jello.
Add the frozen strawberries to jello mixture.
Crumble cake.
Layer cake, then jello mixture.
Layer again; add Cool Whip on top.

title: peanut butter pie(yummy)
directions: Blend peanut butter, cream cheese, sugar and milk together, then fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell.

title: corn flakes treats
directions: Add an immeasurable amount of unselfish love, a generous lot of self respect, a dash of the spice of life and carefully sprinkle throughout with large portion of give and a little take.
Fold in a great deal of patience, tenderness, consideration, understanding and generosity.
Gently blend all together.
Never stir, shake jar or beat.
Spread the mixture smoothly throughout a receptacle called Home.
Be sure to fill every nook and corner.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice, cook, drain and mash squash.
Stir in all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Marinate all ingredients; add tomato and avocado when serving.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple with juice into a buttered 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine flour and sugar and sprinkle over pineapple. Cover with layers of cracker crumbs and cheese.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: five hour stew
directions: Brown meat. Cut the vegetables into large bite size pieces. Combine all ingredients.
Bake in covered dish at 250° for 5 hours.

title: rega's red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans. Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Combine flour, soda, salt and cocoa and gradually add to butter mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Blend well.
Pour into pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, combine the carrots, butter, lemon juice, salt, sugar and a dash of ginger.
Add just enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until liquid evaporates.

title: serbian cabbage(your guests will never guess its cabbage)
directions: Cut eggplant in slices.
Dip in milk, flour, milk and then in bread crumbs.
Deep fry and when cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pecan tassies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together the 1/2 cup butter or margarine and softened cream cheese.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Cover and chill one hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cheese and blend in sour cream and seasonings.
Stir in shrimp and add paprika as desired for color.
Serve with sturdy potato chips or other "dippers."
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix in applesauce.
Add raspberry mixture.
Chill and enjoy.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Place breasts, skin side down, in baking pan.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Turn.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Add tomatoes.
Blend soup, water and seasoning and pour over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes (total time, 1 hour) in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Combine juice and cornstarch in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add margarine and cinnamon and mix well. Stir in apples. Spoon into crust and top with second crust. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable slaw
directions: Thaw and break up the frozen vegetables.
In a large (1-gallon or more) salad bowl, combine all ingredients thoroughly.
The mixture should have the consistency of cole slaw.

Add more yogurt and dressing (in equal amounts) if the salad is not moist enough. Refrigerate overnight, if possible, in an airtight container. This salad is a good main dish for a hot summer day, especially when served with whole grain bread or crackers. This recipe makes about 12 (1-cup) servings and takes about an hour to prepare if the spinach and green beans are already thawed.
It tastes best, however, when chilled overnight before serving.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Rinse clams under running water.
Put clams and reserved liquid in medium saucepan.
Add 1/4 c. water or clam juice.
Add parsley, garlic and olive oil and stir.
Bring to a boil and then simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Put linguine in large pasta bowl.
Pour sauce over and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and drain. Add tomato sauce and let simmer. Cook noodles. Dice onion and add to sour cream. Grate cheese. Use 9 x 13-inch pan and layer as follows: 1/2 noodles, 1/2 hamburger, 1/2 sour cream and onions and 1/2 cheese. Repeat layers. (Use more cheese on last layer.) Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cover and cook 15 more minutes, making sure cheese doesn't get too brown.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Cream sugar, butter and
lemon;
add
beaten egg yolks. Add lemon juice, flour,
Grape-Nuts and milk.
Mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.	Pour
into well-greased dish and set in pan of water.
Bake slowly for
1 hour and 15 minutes or until set.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Dice and cook potatoes until soft.
Combine potatoes, bacon, mayonnaise, eggs, onions, celery, salt and pepper in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan or dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Onions will be somewhat crunchy.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together. Pour over margarine.
Add peaches on top of mixture.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: eggplant-vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion, ground beef and garlic in olive oil in a large stockpot for 5 minutes.
Stir eggplant into mixture and cook 3 minutes.
Add zucchini, carrots, celery, tomatoes, beef stock, oregano, basil, salt, sugar and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 to 2 hours.
Add macaroni and cook 20 minutes more.

title: tapioca
directions: Mix sugar, tapioca, milk and egg in medium saucepan; let stand 5 minutes.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to full boil.
Pudding thickens as it cools.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool 20 minutes; stir.
Serve warm or chilled.
Store left over pudding in refrigerator.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Slice top off green peppers.
Remove seeds and white membrane. Discard.
Cover green pepper shells in pot of boiling water. Cook 5 minutes.
Remove and drain shells.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Beat in egg.
Add flour, soda and salt. Stir in chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 11 to 13 minutes at 375°.

title: gertie's cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine fruit cocktail, egg, and margarine and pour in an 8 x 12 inch greased pan.
Mix brown sugar, chopped nuts, and coconut.
Sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake at 35-40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: In small saucepan, melt oleo.
Stir in pecans and the brown sugar; cook and stir until mixture bubbles.
Spread over bottom of the baked pastry shell.
Cool.

title: martha pafford's egg custard
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour; mix thoroughly.
Stir in milk, water and vanilla.
Pour custard mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 15 minutes.
Chill and serve.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and heat the refried beans.
Pour 1 can of enchilada sauce into browned meat and let simmer.
Take a floured tortilla and spread it with refried beans; add hamburger mix. Sprinkle with grated cheese and then fold it.
Place in long casserole or cake pan.
Repeat process until pan is full.
Pour second can of sauce on top, sprinkle with remaining cheese and place on olives.
Place in preheated oven (350°) until cheese is melted.

title: fish chowder florentine
directions: In large saucepan, combine ingredients; heat thoroughly. Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 12.

title: bread and butter refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and soak 2 or 3 hours.
Drain but do not wash.
Mix together last 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil. Cool.
Pour over pickles.
Put in half gallon jars.
Keep in refrigerator.
Can start eating after 7 or 8 days.

title: hot spiced holiday punch
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except for the lemon slices.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and discard cinnamon stick
and clove. Divide into 4 mugs and garnish with lemon slices.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine biscuit mix, Cheddar cheese and sausage.
Mix well.
Roll or shape into 1-inch balls.
If you want the olives, roll mixture around olive and form ball.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 15 more minutes or until done.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Saut onion and carrot.

title: back and forth cakes
directions: Dissolve soda in syrup.
Sift other dry ingredients together. Stir in syrup and milk.
Pour into greased gem pan or muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: dad t's sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until combined well.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: southern summer cobbler
directions: In 9 x 9-inch pan melt margarine.
Set aside.
Combine flour and baking powder in small bowl.
Add Fruit Sweet and water.
Mix well.
Pour batter over melted margarine.
In another bowl combine fruit, Fruit Sweet and flavoring.
Blend together, then pour fruit mixture over batter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fruit and rice ambrosia
directions: Mix rice, sugar, pineapple, vanilla and marshmallows.
Add apples, cored and chopped (leave peel on) and cherries, cut in half.
Fold in whipping cream.
Chill.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Place margarine and water in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add frozen beans and heat slowly, using a fork to separate.
Cover and cook until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; toss lightly and heat thoroughly.
Celery and onion should remain crisp.
Serves 4.

title: caramel bars
directions: In double boiler, melt caramels and evaporated milk.
In large bowl, mix cake, nuts, melted butter and evaporated milk.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 1/2 of cake mixture in pan. Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chips on top.
Pour caramel mixture on top.
Sprinkle rest of cake mixture on top.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before cutting.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Beat
eggs
and add sweetened condensed milk, sugar and salt. Blend
in cream and add peaches to mixture.
Add enough whole milk to fill container a little over 3/4 full.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: low fat coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease an 8 inch round pan.
Mix together the Bisquick, oats, 3/4 cup of apple sauce, sugar, cinnamon, egg, vanilla and butter, stirring vigorously for 1 minute and spread in pan.
Bake for 30-35 minutes.
While still hot spread with 3/4 cup of the apple sauce and add topping.

title: puppy dog salad
directions: Place lettuce leaf on salad plate; place pear, cut side down, over lettuce.
For ear, place prune on wide end of pear.
Place orange segments along bottom for collar.
Place cherry at narrow end for nose.
Add raisin for eye.
Serve immediately or chill until serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion on medium heat until beef is browned and the
onion is soft. Drain off fat; add season salt, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce, mix well. Press the beef mixture into a 2 qt. casserole dish. Spread the mashed potatoes over the
meat, then top with cheese. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pinana cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 3 round cake pans. Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl. Add oil and eggs. Stir until all dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat. Stir in bananas, pecans, vanilla and pineapple. Divide batter evenly among pans. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes then remove from pans and cool completely. After cooled, ice with cream cheese frosting, mixed with pecans. Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Place in a greased 8-inch casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and butter. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: laredo
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add bell pepper, onion and tomato; brown. When done, add pinto beans, cheese and salsa.
It is
cooked when it comes to a boil.
Serve with hash brown potatoes.

title: date balls
directions: Cook until thick.
Roll in small balls and then roll in coconut and chopped nuts.

title: orange coconut chess pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs, orange juice and coconut.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Grate cheese.
Add chilies and butter.
Melt over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Keep warm on fondue if one is available. Add sliced olives, if desired.

title: orange slice candy
directions: Mix candy, crumbs and
nuts.
Melt
oleo
and marshmallows. Pour over mix and form into
or 4 logs.
Roll in xxx sugar. Wrap in waxed paper and chill before slicing.

title: nachos
directions: Put single layer of chips in a pan.
Top with cheese and place in 350° oven until cheeses are well melted.
Top with salsa. Enjoy.

title: cheese sausage biscuits
directions: Mix well and shape into balls the size of donut holes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until slightly brown.
If frozen, cook at 300° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and pour over confectioners sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cream.
Roll into balls.
Melt in double boiler: 1 package chocolate or peanut butter chips and 1/2 bar paraffin wax.
Remove from stove.
Dip balls in this mixture.
Lay balls on wax paper.

title: spicy applesauce
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Line casserole dish with margarine.
Spread cracker crumbs on bottom of dish.
Pour in layer of onions and layer of soup until all are used.
Mix beaten eggs with milk.
Pour over mixture in casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and a few more cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour drained mixed vegetables over chicken.
Combine soups and broth; pour over vegetables.
Combine flour, milk and butter.
Pour over all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust is brown.

title: apple crunch
directions: Fill baking dish with apples.
Mix water and lemon juice. Pour over apples.
Combine flour, butter, cinnamon and sugar. Stir mixture until crumbles.
Spread over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for about 2 hours or until it begins to bubble and brown. Serve with whipped cream.

title: el gando
directions: Cook ground beef.
Add salt, chili mix and tomatoes.
Simmer until almost dry. Cook rice as directed on package.
Put a layer of meat and tomato mixture in a large serving dish and cover with cooked rice.
Add the rest of the tomatoes and meat.

Heat the can of Cheddar cheese soup and milk and spread over the meat mixture. Sprinkle chopped olives, grated cheese and onion on top along with 2 cups crushed Fritos. Decorate with lettuce and tomato wedges. This complete meal, which serves 10, can be prepared in about 30 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and cook until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and add box of jello.
Set until lukewarm and pour over sliced strawberries in a baked pie shell. Chill and then top with cool-whip.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together thoroughly.
Add crab meat.
Split English muffins and spread mixture over the 12 pieces.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.
Cut in 4 to 6 pieces to serve.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: brunch enchiladas
directions: Combine ham, onion and green pepper.
Place 1/3 cup ham mixture and 3 tablespoons cheese on tortilla.
Roll up and place filled tortillas, seam down, in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Combine eggs, half and half, flour, garlic and Tabasco.
Pour over tortillas.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or several hours. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 4 more minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican skillet casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper; drain.
Chop tomatoes in food processor.
Add along with tomato sauce, seasonings and shell macaroni.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes, stirring more frequently toward end of cooking.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve topped with Parmesan cheese.
Excellent with garlic bread.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown sausage and remove from fat.
Saute vegetables in fat. Add soup and rice to 4 1/2 cups of water.
Cook until done.
Drain off excess water.
Add vegetables and water chestnuts to sausage. Put in large casserole dish.
Top with almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from chocolate pieces.
In large mixing bowl, beat the butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour; blend until smooth. Stir in small chocolate chips.
Mold scant tablespoon dough around each chocolate piece, covering completely.
Shape into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until set.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Cool completely.
Drizzle topping over each cookie.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Parboil cabbage in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Separate leaves and set aside, using 20 leaves.
Mix beef, milk, onion, garlic salt, rice, egg, 1/2 can tomato paste, salt and pepper. Place small cabbage leaf in large leaf.
Place 1/3 cup meat mixture in center of small leaf.
Roll both leaves around meat. Fasten with toothpicks.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Add cabbage rolls.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: uncle bill's molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients accordingly.
Roll on lightly floured board.
Cut and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sorghum tea cakes
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add sorghum syrup and buttermilk; mix well. Combine flour, soda and spices. Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture. Chill 3 hours or overnight. Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on a lightly floured board; cut with a 1 1/2-inch cookie cutter. Place cookies on greased cookie sheets. Sprinkle lightly with additional sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on wire racks. Yield: 9 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and then at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cousin mary's minnesota peach dessert
directions: Mix together flour, butter and 2 tablespoons granulated sugar. Pat into ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cook 1 cup granulated sugar, cornstarch, warm water and light corn syrup until it is thick and clear.
Add lemon jello; stir to dissolve.
Add sliced peaches.
Pour this over the crust and refrigerate.

title: apple caramel pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange apple slices in pie shell. Combine butter, flour, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon in a bowl. Spread mixture over apples.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat shortening and sugar together until creamy.
Add eggs, vanilla, bananas and sour cream; blend well. Sift together dry ingredients and fold into moist mixture.
Mix in chopped nuts. Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 1 hour.
Test middle of loaf before removing bread from oven.
If sticky to the touch, continue to bake a little longer.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Cook cauliflower with salt until tender.
Saute olives, onions and mushrooms in butter, then add the flour.
Stir in milk until it thickens.
Place cauliflower in casserole; pour sauce over the top.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: wilma's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter or oleo in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; set aside. In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour this mixture in the baking pan in which the melted butter was placed.
Now, pour desired fruit and juice on top of batter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy supper
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Pour into baking dish. Top with string beans that have been drained.
Mix cream of chicken soup and milk.
Pour over top of the beans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May be topped with grated cheese or French fried onion rings during the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: lo-fat pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of pans. In a large bowl with fork, mix flour and next 7 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and mix just until blended.
Turn batter into pans. Bake 1 hour for large loaves and inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Makes 2 to 3 large loaves or 5 to 6 mini loaves.

title: quick shrimp scampi
directions: Cook the butter or margarine, garlic, parsley and sherry in an electric frying pan for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in the plain breadcrumbs.
Add shrimp.
Cook over low heat (325°) for 10 minutes, turning frequently.
Sprinkle with additional fresh parsley and serve over rice or angel hair pasta.

title: special steak
directions: In small bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Place steak in shallow baking dish.
Pour mixture over steak and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight to marinate.
Remove steaks; reserve marinade.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine onion, rice and hot broth.
Bring to a boil on top of range.
Cover and place in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves four hungry or six polite people.
Serve and listen to the compliments.
(From Dear Abby newspaper column.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Whisk together all ingredients except pecans.
Stir pecans in last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: oven-baked steak
directions: Pound flour (mixed with salt and pepper, if so desired) into both sides of meat.
With a little bit of oil in a pan, brown both sides of meat.
Spray the bottom of baking pan with Pam and put meat in.
Mix a little amount of water with dry onion soup mix and pour over meat.
Cover with foil.
Bake in slow oven (about 300° to 325°) until desired doneness.

title: new england macaroons
directions: In medium bowl, mix egg white and salt.
Beat until foamy. Gradually add sugar and beat until it peaks.
Fold in oats, coconut, and vanilla.
Drop batter by teaspoonful onto greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until browned.
Remove and place on a cooling rack.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat
in	skillet over medium heat. Drain and set aside. Blend
next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion
and pepper.	Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown or when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together in 9 x 12-inch casserole and top with crushed corn flakes and margarine.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
May store overnight in refrigerator.
Also freezes well. If frozen, remove 1 hour before serving.

title: pizza rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Brown hamburg and onion.
Add tomato sauce, garlic salt, sugar, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: mexican hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain grease.
Put 1 layer of mix, layer of meat, layer of cheese and layer of mix.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: quick and easy raspberry bars (strawberry)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter and mix with cake mix (dry) and oats. This will be very crumbly.
Place 2/3 mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Press down to make an even layer.
Set aside.

title: dump salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Dump remaining ingredients into gelatin mixture, mix well and chill until set.
This is nice served on lettuce leaf.

title: spiced coconut-carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 18 muffin cups with foil liners. Sift first 7 ingredients into large bowl.
