Mix in both sugars, then coconut, carrot, raisins, apple and nuts.
Whisk vegetable oil, eggs and vanilla extract in medium bowl to blend.
Gradually mix oil mixture into dry ingredients, occasionally scraping down sides of bowl.

title: dijon anchovy appetizer
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on slices of French bread.
Broil until lightly browned.
Garnish with green olive slices.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Stir until all ingredients are well blended.
Spread into a greased 9-inch square pan and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix well Wesson oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add apple, nuts, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 1 hour at 300°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Mix oatmeal and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into oatmeal mixture.
Add peanut butter, shortening and egg (just enough to moisten dry ingredients).
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 (2-inch) muffins.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a 12 x 9-inch pan in the oven.
Bring fruit to boil in a saucepan.
In a bowl, beat flour, sugar, baking powder and milk into a batter.
Pour batter into the center of the pan (allow butter to remain on the edges).
Pour the hot fruit into the center of the batter.
Cook for 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: "psita kolokithakia" - stuffed zucchini
directions: Saute meat until lightly browned; add next 5 ingredients plus seasonings and mix.
Stuff zucchini.
Bake with 1 cup water and sprinkle with the juice of 1 lemon.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: mammy's fried pies
directions: Roll pastry 1/8-inch thick.
Cut 4-inch circles or squares. Place a spoonful of the filling on half.
Moisten the edge with cold water.
Fold over and press the edges firmly together.
Fry in deep fat like doughnuts or saute with a little fat in a hot frying pan, turning the pie so that it will brown on both sides.
These are good with fillings of mincemeat or any thick jam or preserve.

title: ma ma causey's old fashioned dropped tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Beat until mixed well.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Mix well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by tablespoon on a well-greased cookie sheet. Cook 10 to 11 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cake with peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon-laced sour cream pound cake
directions: Combine pecans, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon, stirring well.
Set side.
Cream butter; gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Gently fold sour cream into batter.
Pour half of batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle half of pecan mixture over batter.
Repeat procedure.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until cake springs to touch.
Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: peanut butter "cups"
directions: Combine graham crackers and melted margarine.
Mix peanut butter and sugar; mix thoroughly.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt the chocolate over hot water and then spread evenly over the crumbs.
Cool in the refrigerator until firm.
Cuts best at room temperature.
Can be served in a small cupcake paper cup.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp thoroughly and place in a large shallow pan.
Add celery, onion and garlic.
Squeeze juice from 2 lemons over top. Dot with butter and sprinkle with remaining ingredients, except lemon wedges.

title: plain sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Sift again.
Cream butter. Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, beating thoroughly after each. Add vanilla.
Add flour alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Chill.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into desired shape.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 9 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: yummy dough(kids recipe)
directions: Measure brown sugar and peanut butter into bowl.
Squeeze with hands.
Add granola (optional).
Explore dough freely.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar, eggs, oil, salt and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar to first mixture.
Form into balls, roll in sugar and flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian delight cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, using oil, eggs and drained orange juice.
Stir in nuts and oranges.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°, using a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or Pyrex dish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk, and salt to a soft ball stage, 234° - 238°. Add marshmallows and peanut butter just before removing from heat. Do not stir. Cool to room temperature. Add vanilla flavoring. Beat until mixture is creamy and thick. Pour into buttered shallow pan.
Cut into squares. Yield: 2 dozen pieces.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients (except noodles) and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle noodles on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix and bake in loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Bake slowly at 325° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: dip layered nacho
directions: Mix refried beans and nacho seasoning.
Spread in bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spread on sour cream.
Sprinkle on tomatoes, onion, black olives, chilies and Monterey Jack cheese. Serve with corn chips.

title: greasepaint(formula for makeup)
directions: Using
rubber spatula, blend shortening, cornstarch and flour on a white plate to form smooth paste.
Add 3 to 4 drops glycerin for a creamy consistency.
The yield should be enough for a child's face.

title: hidden apple coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch round cake pan.
Combine sugar, chopped nuts and cinnamon.
Separate biscuits into 20 biscuits.
Dip each in melted margarine, then in sugar mixture. Arrange biscuits in prepared pan, overlapping 15 biscuits around outer edge and 5 biscuits in center.
Place 1 slice of apple between each biscuit.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Combine powdered sugar, vanilla and milk until smooth.
Drizzle over warm coffee cake.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix together.
Good on celery and chips.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add well beaten egg, syrup, milk and flour sifted with soda, salt, spices, raisins (cut in halves), nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Spread thinly in well greased and floured shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
While still warm, spread thinly with icing made by moistening confectioners sugar with milk or water and vanilla. When cold, cut into squares or diamonds, then remove from pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil water for noodles.
Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce; heat on low and stir occasionally.
Add noodles to boiling water; cook until softened.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour and stir to mix well.
Add milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vegetables, chicken, salt and pepper.
Stir well. Butter a 9-inch baking dish and pour in filling.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 375° until biscuits brown well.

title: sugar-free cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In saucepan, bring raisins and water to boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Mix well and bake in prepared pan until done, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: waffle whoopie pies
directions: Mix well. Heat waffle iron and spray with "Pam". Bake waffle 2 minutes. Trim edges before cool.

title: reese's chocolate bars
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except chocolate, and put on cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate and pour on top.
Cool.
Cut into squares. (Also can be rolled into balls and rolled in chocolate.

title: onion soup a al parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onions in 4 tablespoons butter or margarine until golden.
Stir often.
Add the stock and boil 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: dinah shore's chicken divan
directions: Place cooked broccoli in an 8 x 8-inch pan or larger.
Place cooked chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix the chicken soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Place shredded cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon bars
directions: Beat together.
Bake in a jelly roll pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting with lemon flavoring.

title: sunny carrot salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.
Can be frozen.

title: chocolate marshmallow fudge
directions: Coat an 8x8 inch pan with Pam.
Stir together sugar, evaporated milk, and margarine.
Bring to a boil in saucepan and reduce heat to medium-law and cook three minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in chocolate and marshmallows.
Remove from heat and stir until smooth.
Pour into pan and refrigerate until firm (about two hours).
Cut into 36 squares and serve.

title: patao coke sauce(sweet and sour)
directions: Combine equal amounts of sugar and water and bring to a boil. Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Chill.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Half biscuits and mix in butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Put biscuits back together and twist.
Put in greased muffin tin.
Follow directions on biscuit can for baking.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into pieces.
Flour steak and brown in skillet. Place in pan for oven.
Add tomato sauce, chopped onion and peppers on top.
Salt and pepper.
Add 1 can water.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Prepare corn as usual.
Drain.
In a skillet, cook and stir onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons margarine until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, paprika, mustard and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk gradually.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in corn and egg.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart dish.

title: quick chowder
directions: Dump all
together and simmer gently for a few minutes. Serves 3 to 4.

title: rice bread
directions: Peel plantains and grate in blender.
In a large bowl, mix grated plantain, cream of rice, baking soda, oil, salt and sugar or honey.
Stir until properly mixed.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls into 10 x 15-inch pan (include sides). Saute onion and peppers and add to hash browns.
Layer sausage (or bits of ham or bacon) and potatoes over crust (no need to thaw potatoes) and grated Cheddar cheese and onion and peppers.
Then top with eggs whipped with milk and dry mustard.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Serve with salsa! Good!

title: apple kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into cake mix (dry) until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan building up slight edges.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Use amount of milk needed according to package directions and cook pudding as directed.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth. Roll graham crackers until fine crumbs.
Melt butter and mix with crumbs.
Line bottom and sides of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour in pudding mixture and cool.
Add fruit, if you like.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then lower oven to 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: cheesy microwave chicken
directions: Season chicken with paprika and garlic salt.
Beat eggs and milk in shallow bowl.
Place bread crumbs and cheese in shallow bowl and blend.
Coat chicken first in egg mixture, then in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in microwave-safe dish and meaty portions to outside of dish.
Drizzle butter over chicken and sprinkle with any remaining bread crumbs.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 5 to 8 minutes.
Continue to cook on 70% power 15 to 18 minutes or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In a bowl, mix the dressing.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss ingredients and put in flat greased casserole.
Top with 1 cup crushed potato chips, 1/2 cup grated cheese and a few almonds. Sliced almonds are more decorative.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Do not overheat to keep celery crisp.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ground beef and macaroni
directions: Combine water and 1 teaspoon salt; bring to a boil and add macaroni.
Cook, uncovered, 6 to 8 minutes.
Do not drain.
Brown ground beef with onion and pepper.
Add to pot with macaroni.
Add remaining ingredients; cover, bring to boil and simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Do not overcook.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli a little in a microwave.
Melt Cheez Whiz, then mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered.
Bake another 15 minutes, uncovered, or until brown and bubbly.

title: acorn cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Form dough into balls and bring to a point.
Bake for 15 - 20 minutes.
Melt caramels and water in a double boiler.
When cookies are cooled, dip in caramel then into nuts.

title: pistachio-pineapple delight(sugar-free)
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into bowl.
Add mix (pudding).
Mix with spoon vigorously 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts.
Spoon into dessert cups.
Pudding will set in 5 minutes. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: spinach and rice
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add spinach; cook.
Add tomato sauce and rice.
Cook until rice is tender.
Serve hot or cold.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until melted; add vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pan.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: chocolate kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend the butter or margarine and peanut butter. Add the white sugar and brown sugar. Add the eggs and vanilla. Stir in the flour, baking soda and salt.

Use level teaspoonfuls of dough and shape into balls. Roll in white sugar. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and press an unwrapped chocolate kiss in top of each cookie. Bake 2 minutes longer. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put flour, sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder into ungreased 8-inch square baking pan.
Stir with fork to mix well.
Add milk and oil.
Stir until well blended.
Sprinkle brown sugar, remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and chocolate chips over batter.
Mix vanilla with hot water and pour evenly over top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes until surface looks dry and brownie like. Serve with a spoon, warm or at room temperature.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mashed yams, except marshmallows.
Put into 350° oven for 15 minutes, then 15 more minutes with marshmallows on top until they brown.

title: mom's banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and milk.
Then add bananas and cream well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well. Add vanilla and crushed pecans; blend well.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.

title: easy turkey pot pie
directions: Mix together turkey pieces, soup, mixed vegetables and turkey stock.
Set aside.
Coat a 13 x 9-inch casserole with the melted margarine.
Pour out excess margarine and reserve for later use. Next, pour vegetable-turkey mixture into the buttered casserole dish.

title: mini pecan pies
directions: Cream butter and cheese; add flour and mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll into 24 balls and press into ungreased tiny muffin pans.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes, slice crosswise into medium thickness. Beat eggs; add milk and mix well.
Add enough salt and pepper to meal to your taste.
Dip tomato slices into egg bath, then shake in corn meal mixture.
Place slices in heated oil, single layer, turning until good and brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and milk; bring to a boil, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Mix in confectioners sugar; beat until smooth.
Chill until firm. Cut in squares.

title: butter crisps
directions: Mix all together.
Chill.
Shape into balls; put on ungreased pan.
Flatten with a fork, sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 325° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: chilled seafood mold
directions: Combine shrimp, mayo, crabmeat, celery, carrots, onion, horseradish, lemon juice and salt;
mix and set aside.
Combine gelatin and 1/4 cup of water in saucepan; let stand 5 minutes. Place over low heat and stir until melted.
Pour into shrimp mixture and stir.
Pour into ungreased mold.
Chill until firm.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased 8 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: angela's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash mushrooms well, then cut stems and chop into tiny pieces.
Mix with all ingredients listed except mushroom caps.
Fill all mushroom caps with mixture.
Cook in a lightly greased baking pan about 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: curry-almond dressing
directions: Process mayonnaise, ginger, curry, garlic, honey, lime juice and white pepper in a blender until smooth. Toss dressing with salad greens and almonds.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Chop onions, green pepper and celery.
Melt margarine in skillet and add chopped vegetables.
Saute until they are soft. Add raw shrimp, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Remember, with seafood you can use more pepper than usual.
Cover and cook 20 minutes or so.
Make a paste of a mixture of cornstarch and water.
Add to pot, stirring constantly.
This should thicken gravy.
Add water until gravy is just right for putting over rice.
Simmer 10 more minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg beating well.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt, mixing well.
Chill.
Form in 1-inch balls rolled in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes and bacon. In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Add this mixture to the potatoes and bacon to coat all potatoes. Transfer to a greased baking pan. Bake, uncovered, approximately 60 minutes, until bubble and light brown on top.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain.
In skillet, saute chuck in butter until brown; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce; remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, spread half of noodles. Pour on 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes or until heated through at 375°.
Serves 6. May be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake
mix, butter and 2/3 cup milk.
Pour half into greased 11
x
14-inch
baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Meanwhile,
melt
caramels
with
1/3 cup milk over low heat. Pour
chips over baked cake.
Pour melted caramels over chocolate chips.
Spread
remaining batter on top.
Bake 15 to 20 more minutes.

title: company eggs(recipe from bill banks)
directions: Cube bread.
Place bread in buttered (greased) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cheese on top.
Beat eggs well and add milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325° to 350°.
May add chopped ham, dried beef or bacon chips.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 baked pie crusts. Refrigerate for 1 hour and enjoy.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: seafoam salad
directions: In a large bowl prepare jello (can substitute half pear juice for half water).
In another bowl or blender, cream large can of pears with large package cream cheese.
Put together both mixtures plus large Cool Whip.
Mix with mixer; place in mold.

title: microwave nacho dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients in microwavable dish.
In separate bowl, combine next three ingredients.
Spread the tomatoes, onions and peppers over the cheese mixture.
Sprinkle 8 to 10 ounces of shredded Cheddar cheese over the top.
Microwave about 5 minutes on High or until top cheese is melted.

title: flavored pralines
directions: Cook all ingredients together on medium heat until soft ball stage (135°), stirring constantly. Add 3 cups pecan halves. Stir and spoon quickly onto wax paper.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion.
Add rice.
Cook until brown.
Add soup, water, mushrooms and oregano.
Stir.
Add to casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked cherry pudding
directions: Spread pie filling in buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top of filling; drizzle with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until top is golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream.
Yields 9 servings.

title: peaches n' cream cheese cake
directions: Combine flour, pudding, baking powder, butter, salt, milk and egg in large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Place peaches over batter.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and reserved juice in small mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon to within 1-inch of edge of batter.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over cream cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Filling will appear soft. Store in the refrigerator.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch square Pyrex dish.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: m&m's color cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars.
Beat in vanilla, water, and egg. Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast in warm water.

title: libby's orange salad
directions: Melt cream cheese with marshmallows in Sprite on low heat. Add other ingredients and chill all in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cut out in squares when ready to serve.

title: triple chocolate-nut brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch square baking pan with foil, leaving a 2-inch overhang.
Spray foil with nonstick cooking spray.

title: pineapple butterscotch cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve syrup.
Mix 1 1/2 cups pineapple with butterscotch chips.
Combine pound cake and pudding mix.
Mix pound cake as package directs, using reserved syrup as all or part of liquid.
Stir in remaining pineapple.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with pineapple-chip mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for 55 to 65 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a heavy pan.
Bring to a full rolling boil stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over med. heat, or until candy thermometer reaches 234°.

title: peanut butter oatmeal squares
directions: Mix
sugar,
cocoa
and milk.
Bring mixture to a boil. Boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat until well mixed.
Add Quick cooking oats.
Drop onto a cookie sheet or press into a pan and cut into squares.

title: super seafood spread
directions: Place seafood of your choice in mixing bowl; break up finely with fork.
Add remaining ingredients, except olives.
Mix well. Chill.
Garnish with olives and additional picante sauce, if desired.
Serve with taco chips.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Sprinkle chicken with oregano, salt and pepper.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Brown chicken in oil in skillet.
Remove chicken, then saute green pepper, onion, garlic, bay leaf, red pepper, salt and rice until rice is brown.
Add tomatoes and chicken broth and bring to boil uncovered.
Put rice and chicken in skillet; cover and cook 1 hour.
Add 1/2 cup water, peas, pimentos and olives; cook 20 minutes longer.

title: baked tomatoes parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to highest setting (475° or 500°).
Spray a shallow nonstick baking tray or cookie tin with cooking spray. Arrange the tomato halves, cut side up.
Sprinkle each half with 1 teaspoon bread crumbs, 1 teaspoon Parmesan, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake uncovered just until topping is browned, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Each half, 35 calories.

title: pasta pierogi
directions: Boil and drain potatoes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Saute onion in oleo until tender.
Add potatoes and noodles and stir until coated with onion mixture.
Top with cheese.
When cheese is melted, serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill well and serve.

title: broccoli shells and olives
directions: Steam broccoli. Prepare both packages of shells and cheese as directed. Add steamed broccoli and black olives. Add grilled chicken breast. Makes about 5 servings. Very Yummy.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in order, blending well.
Fold in egg whites with rubber spatula.
Pour batter into lightly greased ovenproof bowl set in a pan of water.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until pudding turns golden brown and pulls away from sides of bowl.
Makes a light cake with a very rich lemon syrup.
Serves 4.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Cut and peel peaches.
Add into blender until smooth.
Pour other ingredients in blender until mixed well.
Pour in pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls on large pan.
Brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs and pour onto rolls.
Sprinkle sausage evenly onto rolls and eggs.
Top with cheeses to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: my mother's apple dumplings(adelaide barnes)
directions: Peel and core 4 apples.
Put each on a square of pastry.
Fill each apple hole with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon, a little white sugar and a sliver of butter.
Wrap pastry up and around apple.
Use a sliver of lemon on top.
Make a syrup from next 4 ingredients by boiling for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over and around dumplings that have been placed in baking dish. Bake in oven at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
We always have these in the fall.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread cubes and oleo.
Pour into greased casserole and top with bread cubes and melted oleo. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except egg, in medium bowl. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cover with top crust. Crimp or pinch edges to seal. Slit top crust with sharp knife several times. Brush top crust with beaten egg, if desired. Bake at 375° for approximately 40 minutes. Cool about 10 minutes. Serves 3 to 4.

title: german chocolate sheet cake
directions: Grease pan.
Cover bottom with nuts and coconut.
Make cake mix as directed on box.
Spread evenly over nuts and coconut.
Then mix margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Spoon over cake mix.
Cook cake at 300° to 325° until done, about 1 hour.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Use one gallon jar.
Boil and peel four dozen eggs.
Use a heavy toothpick to poke a hole in yolk of boiled egg.
This helps pickling.

title: broccoli, shells and cheese
directions: Cook shells and cheese according to directions.
Cook broccoli according to directions; then drain.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato and mash (do not add milk or butter); add sugar. Roll out like bread dough. Spread with peanut butter (and nuts, if desired). Roll up jelly roll style. Chill. Slice.

title: chicken and "slick" dumplings
directions: Cook chicken or chickens in boiling salted water until tender. Remove from broth.
Let chicken cool.
Debone and set aside.
Put chicken back into broth and bring to a boil.

title: delicious ham sandwiches
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Place ham on bottom of bun.
Spread with sauce; put on slice of cheese, then top with bun.
Wrap sandwiches individually in aluminum foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May be made ahead and refrigerated until ready to heat.

title: dietetic sugar free cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil raisins, dates and apples in scant cup of water for about 3 minutes.
Add shortening; cool.
Add beaten eggs, sweetener, vanilla and baking soda.
Add flour and nuts last.
Mix well.
Chill dough overnight in covered container. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; then add meal, vinegar and milk.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat well until mixed.
Add vanilla last.
Bake in pie crust 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: payday candy bars
directions: Combine and cook until mixture bubbles the syrup and sugar. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth, then add cereal and peanuts.
Spread in buttered pan and cut into bars or drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: fresh strawberries with almond sauce
directions: Whisk together first 3 ingredients until blended.
Top fresh strawberries with dollop of cream and garnish with toasted almonds.

title: granny smith coffeecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, butter, eggs and almond extract.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and blend into cheese mixture alternately with milk.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour apples on batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion together; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into crock-pot.
Cook on low setting 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with pasta, rice or alone.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Note:
This recipe must be made a day before you are going to serve it.

title: hot sausage cheese puffs
directions: Remove casing from sausage, break up in pieces and fry about 10 minutes.
Drain and cool in large bowl.
Add cheese, biscuit mix and water.
Stir until blended.
Roll into round balls about 1 inch in size.
Place on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° until puffed and brown, 10 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 120.

title: pound cake i
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Gradually add and blend in flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Note:
Save a little Mozzarella to sprinkle on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, stir-fry beef in oil until no longer pink. Stir in soup, water and onion soup mix. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Stir in sour cream; heat through (do not boil). Serve over noodles; garnish with parsley, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: easy cherry chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour or spray 9x13 pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl. Stir in dry cake mix, pie filling and oil.
Blend well.
Spread in pan (surface of cake will be lumpy).
Bake at 350° for 38-40 mins. Cool completely.
Make pudding (as for pie).
Let stand 5 minutes until thick.
Spread over cake.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: pepperoni roll squares
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Press 1 package crescent rolls into pan. Mix ingredients. Pour mixture over crescent roll in pan. Top remaining crescent rolls on top of mixture in a lattice design. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: cinnamon applesauce jello
directions: Dissolve candy and jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in applesauce.
Chill until partially set.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and milk.
Fold into jello and chill.

title: halibut beer batter
directions: Mix to consistency you want on your halibut, chicken or pork. Let set for 5 to 10 minutes before dipping your meat.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice in broth and seasonings to taste.
Add other ingredients together with dressing.
May add chopped ham for a main dish.
Serves 6. Can be made ahead and stored in refrigerator.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse soaked lentils.
Cook over medium heat in water.
Chop vegetables and begin adding to lentils.
Add stewed tomatoes.
Add spices.
Cook overnight.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain.
Add soups and taco sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, pour the bag of Doritos and then pour the meat mixture over it.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top and place in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: cannelloni
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, eggs and seasonings.
Fill manicotti shells. Place in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Pour in combined tomatoes, tomato sauce and water over manicotti.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: cashew casserole
directions: Saute the first 5 ingredients but do not brown.
Mix approximately 3/4 of the noodles and the nuts with sauteed vegetables.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour soup over mixture and stir only enough to blend.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: party feta appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread slices.
Toast one side of bread slices.
Spread mayonnaise mixture onto untoasted side of bread slices.
Broil 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serve.
Makes 12 appetizers.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix croutons, water, salad dressing and oleo.
Beat eggs slightly with one cup of milk.
Add to stuffing mixture.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and salt.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend soup and remaining 1/2 cup of milk; pour over the top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: zesty broccoli rice bake
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Cook and drain broccoli. Combine soups and cheese in a saucepan and heat until blended. Combine onion mixture, soup mixture and cooked rice.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or put in a crock-pot for parties.
Can easily be doubled for large groups.

title: christmas toffee bars
directions: Line jelly roll pan with Keebler Cinnamon Crisps graham crackers (about 12 whole, unbroken).
In medium saucepan, combine 1 cup butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar; bring to boil.
Boil 2 additional minutes.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Spoon sauce over crackers and spread;
bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
After removing from oven, take a knife and put the sauce that has melted around the crackers back on the crackers.
Cool slightly and cut apart where crackers are scored.

title: pork roast cajun style
directions: Take knife and make an "X" cut in meat as deep as possible. Take ingredients and stuff into the holes you just cut and let sit overnight.
Brown in an iron pot or heavy pot real slow.
Brown very good, if it wants to burn or stick, add a very little water. When meat is brown, add the rest of onion and bell pepper in a pot.
Cover with water; let cook until tender.
May use cornstarch to thicken gravy.
Serve with rice.

title: shrimp tarragon
directions: Mix together margarine and flour until smooth.
Blend in soup, broth, Sauterne, lemon juice and seasonings.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add shrimp and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter or oleo, egg and salt; mix.
Combine sour cream and soda.
Add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well by hand.
Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: angel rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, yeast, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add the buttermilk, oil and water; beat until moistened. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic. Cover and let rest for 10 minutes. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter. Place on a greased baking sheet.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix.
Store in covered container.
Use 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: tenderloin
directions: Make small cuts in the tenderloin inserting slivers of garlic. Roll in chopped chives.
Place uncut bacon strips on foil.
Place ham slices on top of the bacon strips.
Next place your tenderloin on the ham.
Roll up the tenderloin in the ham.
Stick toothpicks into the strips to hold the meat together.
Wrap in the foil. Place in the oven for 1 hour or 45 minutes on a grill (if using a grill, use indirect heat).
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: amazing apricot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
This salad will keep about 3 weeks if refrigerated.
Good as a salad or over ice cream, waffles, toast, etc.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cut in chunks.
Cook rice as directed on package (omit season packet).
Saute onion in butter; blend in flour, soup and milk for sauce.
Add mushrooms and seasonings.
In large 3-quart casserole, alternate layers of sauce, rice, chicken and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake at 300° to 350° until bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Mix in a saucepan 2 cups boiling water and the 2 cups Bran Buds.
Set aside to soak.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and then the buttermilk and soaked Bran Buds.
Transfer to a very large bowl or pan at least 6-quart size.
Mix and add the flour, soda and salt.
Fold in the 4 cups All-Bran.
Fill greased muffin tins, 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: wild rice with mushrooms
directions: Put all ingredients, except broth, into frying pan.
Heat over medium-high heat to brown, approximately 20 minutes, until almonds are slightly browned.
Add chicken broth; stir.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover tightly and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: aspic ol{2e
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O in hot Clamato juice.	Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: wac hia cookies
directions: Mix oats, peanut butter and vanilla in a bowl.
Take hands and get mixture to a good crumbly consistency.
Mix the sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa on stove.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over oat mixture.
Spoon out on greased cookie sheet.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
Layer bread, cheese, ham, onion, broccoli and pimento in greased baking dish. In a medium bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Blend well.
Pour egg mixture evenly over ham mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Uncover and bake at 325° for 55 to 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and cook until done; save broth.
Set aside until cool.
Slice chicken breast into 2-inch long slivers.
Set aside. In a medium size skillet saute the butter, onion and celery.
Add the mushroom soup.
Cut cheese into small blocks and add to skillet mixture.
Put in the milk, then add chicken breasts.
Stir mixture well and cook until done.
Add mixture to cooked spaghetti noodles.
Put diced tomatoes on top for added taste and color (optional).

title: potato chive rolls
directions: In cup, dissolve yeast and sugar in water; let stand until foamy.
In large mixer bowl, combine sour cream, potatoes, eggs, salt and 2 cups of the flour.
Add yeast and beat at medium speed for about 4 minutes.
Stir in chives.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto floured surface and knead just long enough to work in remaining 1/2 cup flour and make dough elastic.
Place in greased bowl and cover with damp cloth.
Let rise until double in bulk (1 1/2 hours).
Punch down dough.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Bring brown sugar, margarine and milk to hard boil.
Thicken with powdered sugar until desired consistency.

title: zesty italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in roasting pan and brush with melted butter. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon salad dressing mix.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Add vegetables and wine to pan; sprinkle with remaining salad dressing.
Toss to coat well.
Bake for 25 minutes more or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: beef and bean bake
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until brown and crumbly.
Drain fat. Add remaining ingredients except biscuits.
Heat until very hot. Pour into large casserole dish.
Cut each biscuit across and arrange on top of mixture cut side down.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are golden brown, 10 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Add pumpkin; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add nuts and/or raisins.
Pour into a large greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fried banana
directions: Use enough butter to cover bottom of frying pan.
Slice banana.
Cook in butter until golden brown. Turn and brown other side.
Eat and enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add all ingredients to rice and cook on top of stove to melt Cheez Whiz.
Cook in buttered casserole dish on 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Drain all vegetables (canned).
Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar is melted.
Mix vinegar and sugar mixture with oil and salt. Pour this mixture over vegetables (in a large bowl).
Let stand in refrigerator a minimum of one hour before serving.
Preparing the night before and letting this stand in the refrigerator makes it gooder!!!

title: french onion soup
directions: Combine butter, onion, celery and salt in a 2-quart ovenware casserole.
Cover and cook in microwave 8 minutes.
Add broth. Cover and cook 12 to 15 minutes.
Pour into bowls and add toasted bread slices.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter; add sugar, flour, bell pepper and pimentos.
Add this to first 3 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together oil, eggs, sugar, pumpkin pie mix and orange juice.
Then add flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, baking soda, nutmeg, walnuts and raisins (optional).
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 75 minutes (depends on oven). Test with toothpick. Yields about 3 loaves.

title: creamy crunchy veggie dip
directions: Food Processor Directions:
In food processor bowl, with metal blade, or blender container, process cottage cheese and yogurt until smooth.
Stir in radishes, carrot, onion and pepper.
Cover; refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with fresh vegetable dippers.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs and put in 2-quart casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, put buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp skillet
directions: Place soup in an electric skillet.
Pour in water. Cover. Bring to a boil. Stir in rice, shrimp, celery and green pepper. Season with salt and pepper. Cover, bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until it's done.
Garnish with olives.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Thaw hash browns and place in buttered dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with 1 stick of butter.
In another bowl, mix soup, sour cream, cheese and onion; pour over potatoes.
Mix corn flakes with remaining stick of butter and place over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss first 5 ingredients (dry) together with a fork.
Stir in orange rind, apples, raisins and nuts or seeds.
Pour orange juice into 2-cup measure and add buttermilk to make 2 cups.
Add to egg, molasses and oil and stir thoroughly. Stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients with a few swift strokes.
Pour into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full and bake for 25 minutes.
Makes 24 (2-inch) muffins.

title: cheese 'n wiener crescents
directions: Center each hot dog on a crescent dinner roll and roll up. Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: maurine moon's tamale pie
directions: Heat tamales and chili separate.
Add layer of tamales, layer of Fritos and 1 cup grated cheese in baking dish.
Pour chili over tamale mixture until it goes to bottom.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Add layer of cheese with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Lightly brown the beef; add onions and cook until tender, but not brown.
Add drained corn, soup and sour cream, pimiento, salt, and pepper.
Mix well, then stir in noodles.
Pour into 2 1/2 qt. casserole, add melted butter to breadcrumbs and sprinkle over top of casserole.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, cooking oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test if done by touching top of cake with your finger.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs (whole and yolks) until light in color.
Add salt and cold water, beat well.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Put 1/2 cup flour on board and knead.
Divide and roll out thin.
Leave awhile to dry some and then cut in desired width.
My sons make these and grandson is learning, too.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all
ingredients,
except
ginger ale.
Put in milk jugs and freeze.
Remove
from
freezer	about
4 hours before serving so it will be a slush.
Add ginger ale before serving. You	may make this any color you want by adding food coloring. It will come out yellow if no color is added.
Serves 50.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add buttermilk, stirring until well mixed.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness; cut into rounds with a 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes or until golden. Yields 14 biscuits.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in baked or graham cracker crust. Top with Cool Whip. Chill before serving.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and press onto bottom and up sides of 9-inch pan.

title: crabmeat st. augustine
directions: Chop vegetables into medium sized pieces.
Lightly saute in 1/2 to 3/4 stick butter.
Add crabmeat and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and cook until crabmeat is hot.
Serve at once.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra, but do not
cut
off
ends of okra.	Pack in jars. Mix brine.	Boil for
minutes and pour into jars and seal.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in salt, pepper and nutmeg until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: confetti potatoes
directions: Saute zucchini and celery in margarine until crisp-tender (2 minutes).
Add mushrooms and cook 1 minute.
Add cheese, stirring over low heat until melted.
Serve over potatoes and top with bell pepper.

title: never fail lemon pie
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk with lemon juice. Combine with whipped topping. Pour into pie plate. Stand vanilla wafers around the outside edge of pie. Chill overnight.

title: mostaccioli
directions: In
a
Dutch
oven, brown sausage; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce
and mostaccioli; set aside.
In a bowl, combine egg, Ricotta
cheese
and Mozzarella cheese.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, spread one half of the mostaccioli mixture, layer all the cheese over
mostaccioli
and
top with remaining mostaccioli mixture. Bake,
covered,
at
for 40 minutes.
Top with Romano cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: rice
directions: Brown rice in skillet.
Dry.
Stir until golden brown.
Put liquid in microwave; let it get hot.
Pour rice in liquid.
Stir slightly.
Put in oven at 350°.
Cook 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: my version of canadian pork pie
directions: Cook sausage and onion together, crumbling it up as it cooks until cooked through but not browned.
Drain well on paper towels. Peel potatoes, slice and boil just until soft.
Drain and mash with a little milk (should seem a little dry for mashed potatoes). Add the sausage and mix with mixer until mixed well and sausage pieces are quite small.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Leave hamburger in skillet and add other ingredients.
Mix up biscuit dough, roll around to fit on top in skillet.
Bake at 425° for about 45 minutes.

title: rave salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese in large bowl.
Fold in dry jello.
Fold in pineapple.
Put in serving bowl or salad square casserole and set overnight.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
You can substitute fruit or any flavor jello.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, butter, salt and scalded milk slowly.
Add flavoring.
Pour into pie pan lined with unbaked pastry.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake in moderate oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: super bowl chicken
directions: Saute chicken in butter in a skillet.
Place chicken in casserole.
Saute mushrooms and add to chicken.
Add flour to skillet, stir and add chicken broth to thicken.
Pour sauce over chicken and add artichokes.
Set aside and watch 3 quarters of the game.
Then heat oven to 350°.

title: large four layer red velvet cake
directions: Measure flour and soda and mix together. Set aside. Cream oil and sugar in mixing bowl. Add eggs one at a time. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to other mixture. Add vanilla and food coloring. Bake in 4 layer pans that have been greased and floured and lined with parchment or wax paper. Be sure to grease and flour the linings. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until done. Let cool for about 5 minutes before removing from pans.

title: corn or "egg" bread
directions: Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.
During last 2 or 3 minutes, turn heat to broil to brown top of corn bread.

title: 15 minute chocolate cake
directions: Put water, oleo and cocoa in saucepan and let it come to a full boil.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Mix together hot and dry mixtures.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat together and pour into a 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan or 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
While cake bakes, bring to a full boil 6 tablespoons evaporated milk, 1 stick oleo and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup pecans (optional).
Mix together. After remaining cake from oven, cover it with miniature marshmallows before cake cools.
Stream frosting on cake, covering the marshmallows.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Add oats and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Yields 6 1/2 dozen.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, eggs, the spices, raisins and milk.
Mix well; let come to boil.
Cool, then add the soda.
Add the flour, nuts, pineapple and cherries.
Bake 1 hour in a tube pan at 350°.

title: new orleans style crab spread(cocktail spread)
directions: Blend cheeses, onion and lemon juice.
Blend well (no lumps). Add crab and half portion of Worcestershire sauce.
Mix and taste. If you feel that it needs more Worcestershire, add the rest.
Add pepper and Tabasco sauce; blend and taste.
At this point, you may add salt, if desired.
Chill.
Serve with crackers and Melba toast.

title: mushroom crescents
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain and finely chop mushrooms.
Brown in butter.
Stir in seasons, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until liquid evaporates.

title: gillettes (waffle cookies)
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add vanilla and honey.
Add flour and baking powder.
Can be mixed ahead and kept in refrigerator.
Drop by teaspoons on hot waffle iron and bake. Keeps well and will freeze.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: frozen cucumber relish
directions: Bring to a boil the following, and pour over the above: 1 Tbsp. celery seed, 2 cups sugar, 1 cup vinegar.
Put into container and freeze immediately.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Beat egg yolks and add to white sauce.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
May be served with additional White Sauce, if desired.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine soup, milk, soup mix and mushrooms.
Stir until blended.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Stir rice and thawed vegetables into remaining mixture.
Spoon vegetable mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Pour reserved 1/2 cup soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle paprika over all.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender and chicken is cooked through. Makes 4 servings.

title: nana's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix with beater until thick.
Pour into pie shells; bake at 350° until firm.
Makes 3 pies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage; drain.
Butter bread on one side.
Arrange 6 slices, buttered side up, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover bread with half of sausage and half of cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together and cover cheese with half of egg mixture.
Repeat layers, first beginning with bread and ending with egg mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Can be prepared the night before serving and refrigerated overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Rinse frozen hash browns. Mix hash browns, soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, 6 tablespoons melted butter, salt and pepper. Spread in 4-quart baking dish. Mix 2 tablespoons melted butter and corn flakes. Spread on top of other mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: bourbon pound cake
directions: Combine raisins, fruit and bourbon in a bowl; soak several hours.
Grease and flour a 10-inch angel cake tube pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and nutmeg onto waxed paper.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in the flour mixture alternately with the milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Stir in fruit, bourbon and nuts.
Turn into the pan. Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 2 hours and 10 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in the pan on a rack for 20 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.
Wrap the cake in bourbon soaked cheesecloth and over wrap with foil.
Store in the refrigerator for 3 to 4 weeks.
Frost with glaze, if you wish.

title: crock-pot spicy beef stew
directions: Place cabbage in crock-pot.
Place chuck roast on top of cabbage.
Combine soup, onion, catsup, salt, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, garlic, chili powder, oregano and mix well.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Remove roast from pot and set aside.
Cover pot and turn temperature to high.
Combine water and flour and add to crock-pot and stir until thickened.
Slice roast and return to crock-pot for 10 minutes.
Serve over bread roll, rice or noodles.

title: oven-roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In bottom of broiler pan, without rack, combine all ingredients.
Roast 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple and orange slices, saving juices.
Measure juices and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Heat to boiling.
Put jello into large mixing bowl and pour hot juice mixture over it, stirring until well dissolved.
Add cream cheese and beat until mixture is smooth.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Add pineapple, orange slices, grapes and marshmallows.
Pour into mold or serving dish and chill until firm.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain thawed spinach in paper towel.
Roll up and squeeze out excess moisture.
Mix all ingredients together and serve with chips, crackers or veggies.

title: mac-n-cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain. In a large bowl, shred cheeses on macaroni and stir gently. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix in pats of butter. Pour into baking dish of gallon size. Pour over milk. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more if needed.

title: tom's favorite fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk, chocolate and syrup in a saucepan.
Bring to the boiling point and let boil until mixture will form a soft ball when tried in cold water.
Remove from fire.
Add butter, letting it form a film over the fudge.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Beat until candy loses its glossiness.
Knead on bread board; shape into 2 long rolls.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices when cool.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook sausage and bacon until cooked through.
Drain well.
In large bowl beat eggs and milk together.
Stir in sausage-bacon mixture, mustard, bread and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot cooking oil.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: colorado apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 1 hour 45 minutes at 325° in a tube pan.

title: texas tortillas
directions: Place all ingredients, except flour tortillas, in food processor.
Process until smooth.
Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Roll tortillas in damp paper towels and place in refrigerator.
Chill.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch pieces.
Place on plate with hot sauce.
Contains 41 calories per slice.

title: cajun potatoes
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Add 2 chopped onions, bell pepper and celery.
Cook vegetables about 5 minutes with bacon.
Add potatoes and then green onions and parsley.
Cook over low heat and stir often.
Add cayenne pepper to taste.
If more seasonings are desired, add a little salt.

title: baked beans
directions: Pan-fry onion and ground beef.
Add last 4 ingredients.
Mix with canned pork and beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to
400°.	Beat
eggs
until well blended. Stir in	oil
and
vanilla.
Blend
in
sugar
until
mixture thickens. Sift flour,
baking powder and salt together.
Stir into oil mixture.
Drop
by	teaspoon
about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Carefully press each cookie flat with bottom of glass that	has been dipped in sugar.
Moisten glass with oil, then dip in sugar for extra crunchiness; pat several times.
Bake 8
to
minutes.
Remove from pan immediately. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: dumplings
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Slice biscuits into thin strips. Drop into boiling chicken broth, one at a time.
Mix four with 3/4 cup hot water and stir into dumplings.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: cheese onion bread
directions: Mix egg and milk; add Bisquick.
Stir just until moistened. Add parsley flakes, half of the cheese and chopped onion.
Spread in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Drizzle melted butter over top, about 1/4 cup.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, white sugar and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together and add the flour, salt and soda. Add to the creamed mixture the oatmeal, nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in juices (heated) from cherries and pineapple.
Mix all cherries, pineapple and nuts, then Coke. Grate frozen cream cheese over top.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: honey-of-a-fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat.
Mix cocoa with cornstarch; stir into butter.
Pour honey and water into chocolate mixture. Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and salt.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Serve over ice cream.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: spinach salad
directions: Arrange spinach and mushrooms on 4 plates.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Drizzle over salads.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on box.
Scramble eggs in butter on low heat.
Add diced onion and simmer.
Add cooked rice and soy sauce, if desired.

title: pork tenderloin with balsamic-cranberry sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Melt 1/2 tablespoon butter in heavy large ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle pork with salt and pepper. Sear pork on all sides, about 2 minutes. Place skillet with pork in oven. Roast pork until thermometer inserted into center registers 155°, about 10 minutes.

title: italian bean and tomato salad
directions: Combine beans, tomatoes and dressing. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Sprinkle with basil and cheese just before serving. Makes 6 servings, 1 cup each.

title: italian bake
directions: Brown burger; drain.
Cook noodles as directed.
Add Ragu to burger, then spices.
In casserole dish, layer burger mix, noodles and cheese; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese is golden.

title: nanie's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour together well, looks like cocoa. Add 1/2 cup milk and mix.
Add beaten eggs, then 1 cup milk and vanilla; mix.
Cook until thick, stirring all the time.
If lumps appear, keep stirring harder.
Put in baked pie shell and chill.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan and put coconut and nuts in bottom of pan. Prepare mix according to package. Pour over coconut and nuts. Mix oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar; put on top, using teaspoon. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: scones
directions: In small bowl, stir together eggs and 1/3 cup milk.
Reserve 2 tablespoons.
Add remaining egg mixture to the flour, mixing with fork until dough forms.
With hands, carefully pat dough into 6-inch squares, 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 3 x 3-inch squares.
Cut each square into 2 triangles.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Brush with the reserved 2 tablespoons egg mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yield:
8. Good!

title: taco fondue
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add the tomatoes and green chilies and the green chilies and stir.
Then add the cheeses and melt.
Serve hot with Tostitos, Fritos or bread cubes.
Good with raw vegetables, too!

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the oleo until light and fluffy, then whip in the sugar. Add the mashed bananas and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, salt and soda mixture.
Turn into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes, or until done.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, margarine, salt and cream of tartar. Boil over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir into popcorn until hard, 2 minutes.
Stir in roaster.
Spread on two greased cookie sheets.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Pour chips in unbaked pie shell.
Melt margarine.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Pour over chips in pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm, approximately 45 minutes.

title: apple streusel pie
directions: Combine ingredients, except apples.
Toss with apples.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.

title: ballpark baked beans
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans, brown sugar, ketchup and mustard. Transfer to a 2 qt. baking dish. Bake, uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir in pineapple, bake for 30 minutes longer. Serve.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding.
Add oil (shortening), milk and water.
Using the number of eggs indicated on package of cake mix, beat yolks and whites separately.
Add beaten yolks to mixture first, followed by beaten egg whites.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom-lemon filets
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pam 12 x 8-inch or 8 x 8-inch baking dish. In large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons margarine or use Pam.
Saute the mushrooms and onions until tender.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in flour, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly until smooth and bubbly.
Gradually stir in the milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in lemon peel.
Place fish fillets or pan fish in baking dish.
Spoon sauce over fish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Mix Coke and catsup.
Pour over chicken and simmer until tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and jello.
Add oil, water and strawberries.
Add egg yolks one at at time.
Beat whites until stiff.
Fold into mix and pour into pan (greased).
Start with cold oven, 275° for about 1 hour.
Use sheet cake pan.

title: cranberry oatmeal brownies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, eggs, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking soda and stir well.
Grease a large cookie sheet.
Spread dough into cookie sheet pressing it to about 1/2 inch thick.
Spread cranberry sauce over the dough within 1 inch of edges.

title: banana cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 25 minutes.
Fifty calories per cookie.

title: salsa burger subs
directions: You will also need 6 pieces of aluminum foil.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease casserole dish.
Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Beat 20 strokes and spread in dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over batter.
Bake until set, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into a loaf.
Bake at 325° for 30 - 45 minutes.
This can be made the night before and set overnight in the refrigerator and baked the next day.
This mixture can also be used to stuff green peppers.
Makes enough for 2.

title: scalloped broccoli and corn
directions: Arrange the broccoli spears, crosswise, in a greased, 8 x 12-inch,
glass baking dish or cake pan.
Combine the corn, half of	a can of French fried onions and the remainder of the ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.

title: tangy pasta and cheese salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain well. Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, and seasoning, set aside.
combine other ingredients (do not cook peas).
Toss with yogurt mixture.

title: tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef and chili powder until the beef is browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.

title: hodge podge
directions: Layer these vegetables in the order listed in a kettle the size and amount of vegetables suitable for your family.
On top, put 2 or 3 sticks of oleo and add enough water to see around vegetables.
(You want it to cook down to a small amount). Cover and cook until almost tender; uncover to boil water way down.
Add enough cream to cover well; stir carefully.
Serve with hot biscuits!

title: diet macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onion and pepper; cook until soft, not brown, 4 to 5 minutes.
Whisk in flour; sir in milk, pumpkin, 1 cup water, broth mix and thyme.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened and just boiling.

title: carrot casserole no. 2
directions: Sprinkle
herb
dressing
over the top after mixing the ingredients together.
Bake at 300° to 325° about 25 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: In pan, fry hamburger with celery and onions. Drain. Add remaining ingredients. Stir. Simmer 1/2 hour or longer.
Serve on buns.

title: oatmeal date cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator pan rolls
directions: Combine 3/4 cup hot water with sugar, salt and margarine; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add to water-sugar mixture; add egg and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough flour (about 2 3/4 cups) to make soft dough. Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and turn to grease top.
Cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator or until doubled in bulk (until needed, may be kept 4 to 5 days).

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread and roll on a cookie sheet like a pizza.
Mix next 7 ingredients together and spread on dough like a paste.
Next, layer pepperoni, ham and cheeses.
Roll up like a jelly roll. Place on cookie sheet, seam side down, and brush with the reserved egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Slice and serve. Excellent!

title: ukrainian sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg yolks and sour cream.
Sift dry ingredients, using enough flour so dough can be easily handled.
Roll thin; cut into desired shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Beat peanut butter and butter until smooth, about 1 minute. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips. Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Immediately sprinkle remaining chocolate chips over cookie layer.
Let stand 5 minutes or until chocolate chips become soft. Spread evenly over the top. Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: insalata agro-dolce(sweet and sour italian salad)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Stir lightly. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 20.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Split chilies and seed.
Line 2-quart casserole with a layer of chilies, add a layer of mixed cheeses.
Repeat until all chilies and cheese are used, but end with chilies.
Beat egg yolk and canned milk and pour over chilies and cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in the flour.
Spread this on top.
Cover the whole thing with tomato sauce.
Bake at 325° exactly 1 hour.
Let set for 10 to 15 minutes before eating.

title: party dessert
directions: Combine fruits, juices, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into refrigerator tray (or loaf pan) and freeze until firm.

title: hot seafood dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with bland, very crisp crackers.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese and mix with other ingredients.
Roll mixture out in a thin sheet.
Cut in narrow strips, 4-inches long.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: In saucepan, combine carrots with chopped onion and boiling water.
Bring all to boiling and reduce to simmer.
Cover and cook until carrots are tender.
Drain and puree in blender.
Return pureed mixture to saucepan and stir in flour, butter, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Gradually blend in milk, stirring until smooth. Heat, stirring constantly until soup reaches boiling point.
Serve while hot and add sprinkling of fine parsley.
Serves 4 people.

title: petite cheese cakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Line muffin tins with cupcake papers.
Pat vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cup.
Fill 2/3 full with cheese mixture.

title: mexican pizzas
directions: Place tortillas one at a time in nonstick skillet.
Layer cheese and remaining ingredients over tortillas as desired. Cook, covered, over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 servings.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients. Put in oven at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Last 1/2 hour in oven, put pineapple slices on top.

title: fresh peach-raspberry cobbler
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the sugar, cornstarch and water. Stir.
Add peaches, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Gently fold in raspberries.
Return to boiling, but avoid breaking up fruit.
Pour into shallow 2-quart casserole.
Drop on the topping.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes with onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Mix with Italian salad dressing.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Just before serving, add mayonnaise, celery and eggs. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chow mein noodle hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion and celery in skillet.
Add cans of soup and mixed vegetables.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles and return to oven for 30 minutes more.
I use a little soy sauce also.

title: fajitas
directions: Marinate steak in the next 7 ingredients for 4 hours or overnight.
Tie green onions together and use as a brush.
Place meat on grill.
Baste using the onion brush.
Cook onions 6 to 8 minutes.
Cook the meat 3 to 5 minutes on each side.
Roll onion brush in marinade; grill 3 to 5 minutes.
Cut beef in strips across the grain.
Serve in tortillas with beans, salsa, guacamole, sour cream and cilantro.

title: beer pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet; drain.
Brown chopped onion and celery in same skillet.
Add soup, mushrooms and beer; bring to a slow simmer (do not boil).
Place chops in crock-pot and pour soup mixture over.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Cook on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Excess gravy can be used on mashed potatoes or rice.
May also be made in oven.

title: blueberry puffs
directions: Prepare muffins as directed on our wild blueberry muffin mix package, except bake batter in tiny muffin cups, 12 to 15 minutes. Mix sugar and cinnamon. Roll hot muffins in 1/2 cup melted butter, then in cinnamon-sugar mixture. Makes about 24 small muffins.

title: bakeless fruit cake
directions: Mix marshmallows and cream; soak overnight.
Mix 1/2 of mixture with 1 pound graham crackers crumbs.
Mix the other half of mixture with all the rest of the ingredients.

title: carolyn's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together potatoes, sugar, melted butter, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, butter, and chopped nuts and put on top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together and beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour alternately with lemon extract and 7-Up.
Begin with flour and end with flour.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. When thoroughly cooled, sift powdered sugar over cake.

title: stewed zucchini medley
directions: Saute onion.
Add fresh tomatoes (or 1 can stewed tomatoes), zucchini, green pepper, salt and pepper to taste and 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Cook until vegetables are soft, about 10 minutes.
Thicken with 1 teaspoon cornstarch.
Excellent with meat loaf or fish.

title: easy doughnuts
directions: Heat vegetable oil on medium heat.
Separate biscuit dough. Flatten slightly and poke a hole in center.
Fry a few at a time until golden.
Drain on paper towel.
Shake in small paper bag with sugar and cinnamon or confectioners sugar.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix and add reserved liquid.
Pour into a casserole.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: white coffee cake
directions: Put vanilla pudding into large bowl and beat in the eggs.
Add cake mix and stir until all lumps are mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle the butterscotch morsels and pecans evenly over the cake.
Take pancake turner and mash them down slightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: israeli sweet and spiced chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat oil; in batches, brown chicken pieces on all sides.
Over bottom of shallow 3-quart casserole, spread onion slices; top onions with chicken pieces.
In a 2-cup measure of bowl combine juice, honey and seasonings; pour mixture evenly over chicken and top chicken with olives.
Cover casserole and bake until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Combine cookie mix with brown sugar, butter, egg and vanilla. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips; spread when melted. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach in microwave oven, then drain.
Chop onion fine. Melt margarine.
Mix all of the ingredients together.
Let chill for 1 hour.

title: georgia corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Remove core of cabbage.

Place it in a large kettle of boiling water. Cover and cook 3 minutes or until softened enough to pull off individual leaves. Cut thick center stem from each leaf. Place meat, rice, salt, onion and pepper in a bowl and mix thoroughly.
Place a heaping tablespoonful on each leaf.
Tuck sides over filling while rolling leaf around filling. Place a trivet in large Dutch oven.
Put in cabbage rolls.
Pour tomato sauce and 1 can of water over and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana bars
directions: In large
mixer
bowl,
cream sugar and margarine.
Add oats, flour and
soda; beat well.
Stir in sour cream, vanilla and banana.
Pour
batter
into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: butterfinger torte
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Stir in beaten egg yolks, fold in whipped cream.
Mix candy and nuts.
Cover the bottom of a cake pan with 1/2 of an angel food cake (broken into bits or slices).
Cover this with 1/2 of the first mixture, then 1/2 of the second mixture.
Repeat.
Chill overnight.
Can be frozen.

title: basic stir-fry
directions: In a glass bowl, combine chicken, soy sauce and garlic powder. Stir well and set aside.
Heat 2 teaspoons oil in skillet or wok. Stir in all vegetables and stir-fry 3 to 5minutes until onions are translucent.
Remove to bowl.
Heat remaining 2 teaspoons oil; add chicken and stir-fry until chicken is cooked, about 5 minutes. Return vegetables to skillet.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and continue cooking until sauce thickens.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 9 x 5
x 3-inch.
Beat all ingredients on low speed, scraping bowl constantly,
seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 1 minute.

title: broccoli cheese squares
