directions: Steam broccoli 5 minutes or until tender-crisp; do not overcook.
Cool and chop fine.
In a large bowl, beat eggs; add flour, milk, baking powder and salt; mix to blend.
Stir in cheese and steamed broccoli and onion.
Melt butter and coat bottom of an 8-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Spoon mixture into pan; spread evenly.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.
Cut into 6 squares for a side dish or 20 to 24 small squares for appetizers.

title: 3 ingredients cookies
directions: Mix sugar and egg together until creamy.
Add peanut butter until well blended.
Shape by teaspoonful into a ball.
Bake about 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: turtle cookie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2/3 cup butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Pour hot syrup over crust layer after you have sprinkled pecans on.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let it stand 5 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: 1 bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° if glass dish).
Melt chocolate and margarine in a large microwaveable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine melts.
Stir until chocolate melts.
Stir sugar into chocolate; blend well.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° (or 325°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.
Makes 24 squares.

title: best pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine and mix all the ingredients, one at a time, in order given.
Pour into unbaked (9-inch) deep dish type pie crust.

title: parmesan pepper wreath
directions: Place 1/2 cup warm water in large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add remaining water, sugar, pepper, salt and 1 cup flour; blend well.
Stir in whole egg, Parmesan cheese, and enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 4 to 6 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in size (30 to 45 minutes).
Punch dough down.
Remove dough to lightly floured surface, divide into 3 equal pieces.
Roll each piece to 28 inch rope; braid ropes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Form braid into circle; pinch ends together to seal. Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in size (20 to 40 minutes).
Brush with egg white.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheese rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, 1/2 length of time. Drain, add green chilies and sour cream mixture and 1/2 pound grated cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Top with remaining cheese; cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honeyed carrots with bacon
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring 3/4 cup water to a boil.
Add carrots.
Cover and simmer over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Drain carrots. In same saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in carrots and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 7 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: marshmallow-orange fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together well and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple; put juice in top of double boiler.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add to beaten egg.
When well blended, stir into heated juice.
Add margarine; stir until thick.
Cut cheese into small cubes.
Combine cheese cubes, marshmallows and pineapple chunks.
(Cut pineapple chunks smaller if you like.) Pour cooked mixture over cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: vegetable minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Roll dough on a floured board as you would for pizza, about 1/2-inch thickness.
Spread broccoli on top of dough.
Add sausage, then Ricotta and sprinkle with black pepper and salt.
Roll dough as you would for a jelly roll, pressing slightly as you roll; seal the ends.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Place cooked and peeled chilies in greased casserole; sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese and add creamed corn.
Top with cornbread mix. Bake at 425° until bread is brown; add rest of cheese and bake until hot.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening with firmly packed brown sugar; add eggs (well beaten), soda (dissolved in boiling water) and vanilla.
Mix flour and oats together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° (in hot oven) for about 18 minutes.

title: oatmeal caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine oats, flour, sugar, cinnamon and egg; mix well.
Cut in margarine/butter until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save broth.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix margarine and stuffing mix together.
In casserole dish, arrange as follows:
1/2 stuffing mix/margarine, 1/2 chicken, 1 can of soup, 1/2 can of broth, 1/2 chicken, 1 can of soup, 1/2 can of broth and 1/2 stuffing mix/margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: molded corn beef salad
directions: Make Jello and set aside to cool.
Break corn beef apart with a fork and add chopped vegetables, eggs, salt and mayonnaise.
Mix all with Jello and garnish with chopped pimento and chill until set.

title: pepper spread
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Mix to thin paste. Cook 5 minutes more.
Makes approximately 8 pints.

title: pot roast
directions: Cut slits in meat and insert onion and garlic.
Place meat in bowl and cover with vinegar. Cover and place in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours (baste occasionally).
Pour off vinegar. In a heavy pan, brown beef in oil until very dark.
Pour coffee and 2 cups water over roast. Cook slowly on top of stove for about 6 hours. Add more water as needed. Good.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Melt margarine and sugar together but do not cook.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add vinegar and vanilla and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Tastes like a pecan pie.)

title: southern biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add shortening and mix with pastry mixer.
Add milk and roll out not too thin. Bake in 475° oven.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in 1 c. water until tender; drain and reserve 1/2 c. liquid. Add reserved 1/2 c. liquid, butter, and syrup to carrots; let simmer for 5 minutes.

title: southern rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Slowly add sugar and continue beating until sugar is dissolved.
While stirring, add vanilla to milk, then pour mixture over eggs and sugar.
Be sure to stir well to mix all of the ingredients.
Add the cooled rice.
Be sure there are no lumps in the mixture.
Stir to continue mixing.
Add raisins (optional). Top with pats of butter around edge and middle so that it will melt evenly.
Bake in heated oven for 40 minutes until mixture is a light brown and bubbly on top.
Remove from oven and allow to cool.
Serve with cinnamon or nutmeg if desired.

title: baked stuffed whole lobster
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Plunge 2 live lobsters headfirst into enough boiling, salted water to cover.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from water; place lobster on back on cutting board.
With sharp knife, split lengthwise from head down to base of abdomen.
Spread body open and discard all organs in body section except brownish green liver and red coral roe.
Remove black vein.
Crack large claw.
Combine bread crumbs, butter, Parmesan cheese and onion. Spoon into body cavities.
Place lobsters, shell side down, in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° till lightly browned and meat is cooked, 30 to 35 minutes.
Pass melted butter.

title: sour cream frosting
directions: Melt chocolate pieces and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat; blend in sour cream, vanilla and salt.
Gradually add confectioners sugar to make spreading consistency, beating well.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls and shape into logs. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in low oven at 300° to 325° for about 25 minutes.
Roll in 4x sugar when warm and again when cool.

title: wet burritos
directions: Fry beef with onion.
Drain.
Add refried beans and taco mix with 2 cups water.
Let simmer. Then put enchilada mix and water as directed on package in large saucepan.
Let dissolve.
Add tomato paste and beef gravy.
Let thicken.
Set aside.
Warm tortillas and wrap meat mixture along with lettuce and tomato inside.
Place on a heavy plate, cover generously with sauce and top with cheese.
Heat in 350° oven for 8 minutes to melt cheese. Sauce mix is for approximately 16.

title: pickled red cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in fourths and discard center stalk.
Shred cabbage finely.
Layer in a colander with salt and let stand overnight.

title: lemon pie
directions: These recipes call for starting with a baked 9-inch pie shell. Again I prefer Albertsons ready-made crust.
Remove one crust from the package and let warm up to room temperature, about one hour should do it.
Remove a single crust and unfold.
Prepare pie dish by spraying with Pam all natural spray.
Wiping off excess spray with a paper towel.
Unfold the pie crust--repair any tares by following the makers instructions.
On the side of the crust that will face down on the pie dish put a heaping teaspoon of flour. Spread the flour evenly from the center of the crust to the very edges of the crust.
Brush off excess flour; place floured side down in pie dish.
Carefully fit crust into pie dish.
Cut off excess crust, crimp edges of crust onto lip of pie dish using a table fork.
Also you can use pie rings on edge for excellent results.
Baste crust lightly with milk and bake to makers instructions.
This should give you a beautiful golden brown crust. Let crust cool completely.

title: jalapeno peach dip
directions: *You can buy a 2 cup pkg of the combination.

title: bread puddin'
directions: Soak bread in milk, then add all ingredients together.
If anymore ingredients are needed, they are to be added to taste. Bake in 375° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: chinese chews
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in a large double boiler.
When melted, add peanuts and noodles.
Mix until well coated and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or foil.

title: pretzel salad dessert
directions: Mix together crushed pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter; spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan, pressing firmly to bottom and sides of pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes; let stand until cool.
Mix jello with boiling water until jello is dissolved.
Add pineapple with juice and frozen raspberries; chill until soft set. Mix together softened cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and thawed dairy topping.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled pretzel crust; pour jello mixture over the top and spread evenly.
Chill until firm.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheddar shrimp casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute mushrooms until browned well. Stir in curry and onion powder.
Brown from heat and stir in wine. Blend sour cream and 1 cup grated cheese.
Stir shrimp and onions into sour cream mixture.
If using cooked shrimp, drain well. Toss lightly with well drained mushrooms.
Heap mixture lightly into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until cheese is melted and casserole bubbly.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line 12 muffin cups with baking cups, or grease bottoms of pan.
Beat egg slightly in medium bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients except blueberries just until moistened. Fold in blueberries.
Divide batter evenly among cups.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until golden brown.

title: molasses cookies(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg and molasses. Mix soda and spices with sifted flour; combine. Roll into small balls; roll in sugar. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cook meat in any type oil 2 to 3 minutes or until done.
Add all, except soy sauce cornstarch.
Cook couple minutes until vegetables are soft.
Reduce heat and add beef broth.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: west of the pecos enchiladas
directions: Brown beef. Add salt. Cool slightly and add 1/2 of the cheese. Add the onions and olives. Combine tomato sauce, tomato soup, tomato paste, water, oil, chili powder, garlic powder and salt. Bring to a boil, then simmer. Dip tortilla in sauce. Lay on plate. Place a heaping spoonful of meat mixture on tortilla. Roll. Place in a greased baking dish.
Pour 1 cup sauce over tortillas. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: beet borscht
directions: Chop and fry bacon and drain.
Saute onion and celery.
Simmer first 11 ingredients until tender.
Puree vegetables and add to broth.
Saute grated beets and carrots in 2 tablespoons of butter and saute cabbage in 2 tablespoons of butter for 5 minutes.
Add to soup.
Simmer 15 more minutes.
Add lemon juice, taste for seasoning.
Just before serving, heat to boiling and add dill. Dish up with a spoonful of sour cream for each serving.
Serve with black bread and sweet butter.

title: streusel topped sweet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes with syrup and orange peel.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
In a glass bowl, melt margarine in microwave.
Add soup mix.
Mix well.
Add pretzels gradually, stirring until coated.
Spread pretzels in a 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: sour milk or buttermilk waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine beaten eggs with milk; add to dry ingredients.
Mix.
Stir in melted butter.
Pour batter onto preheated waffle iron.
Bake until crisp.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and oil. Add sugar and beat well. Add egg yolks and beat. Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla, coconut and nuts. Fold in egg whites. Pour into 3 by 8 inch pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: korean beef stew
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together. (Note:
Marinate the beef for at least 1 hour or longer.)
When ready to cook, add just enough water to cover the meat.
After sauce reaches the boiling point, reduce the heat and simmer until tender.
Add the cubed radish and carrots.
Skim off fat.
Add the sesame seeds and spring onions. Serve with rice.

title: chicken with cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease iron skillet and heat.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients for cornbread (first 5 ingredients).
Blend well; pour into prepared skillet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Boil chicken until tender; remove meat from bones.
Set aside meat and broth.
Crumble cooked cornbread in large pan.
Add 4 slices of bread.
Pour chicken broth over hot bread.
Mix well; add chopped onion, celery, meat and cream of chicken soup and bouillon cubes.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan (greased pan).
Bake about 30 to 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.
(Will be very moist.)

title: bread machine easy french bread
directions: Follow instructions on bread machine.
May be used with delay or rapid cycle.

title: dill dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Cream together sour cream, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: creamy pimento cheese
directions: Combine cheese in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer.
Add mayonnaise and a dash of garlic powder (optional).
Mix well.
Stir in pimentos.
Serve at room temperature for best consistency.
To store, cover and chill. Yield:
4 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, onion and bacon to small pieces.
Mix and toss with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: planters punch
directions: Mix orange juice, lemon or lime and rum.
In shaker or blender, add sugar and grenadine.
Shake or blend until frothy. Serve over shaved ice.
Garnish with orange or cherry.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine gelatin with boiling water and dissolve thoroughly. Fold strawberries, pineapple and bananas in juice. Put half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze for 1 to 1 1/2 hours (until firm).
Keep other half warm on sink. Remove first half from freezer and spread sour cream over top of mixture and then gently spoon on the second half of mixture.
Freeze or refrigerate and serve icy cold.
Serves 18.

title: quiche
directions: Layer ham, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Combine baking mix, milk, eggs, salt and pepper in blender.
Process until smooth. Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into wedges.

title: skillet scalloped potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch cubes.
Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add potatoes and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
While they cook, stir about 2 or 3 times.
Add boiling water and Pet milk; cook 20 to 30 minutes over low heat.
Stir once or twice. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into serving dish.
Sprinkle snipped parsley over top.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup and all ingredients, except water and mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place in a shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Spoon off fat.
Mix remaining soup, water and the mushrooms; pour over meat.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Slice steak into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Sprinkle meat with garlic salt and add to oil.
Cook rapidly for 1 minute or until lightly brown.
Remove meat from skillet and add peppers and onions to oil.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring often.
Add soy sauce, tomato sauce and sugar.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes and return meat to skillet.
Cook until meat is heated.
Serve over rice.

title: company meat loaf
directions: Combine soup mix, beaten egg, bread crumbs and milk.
Mix in meat.
Shape into round ring in baking dish.
Brush with mixture of catsup, mustard and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a buttered baking dish.
Sift together ingredients and then cut in butter until a fine crumbly mixture forms.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples and bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: After frying a pan of country ham, add a little water to the drippings. Bring to a boil and serve with ham. You may add about 1 teaspoon of strong coffee for color.

title: jalapeno pimiento cheese
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a large bowl and enjoy. This is a great pimiento cheese recipe.

title: old-fashioned apple butter(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Wash, core, peel and quarter apples.
Place apples and apple juice in a lightly oiled crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for 10 to 18 hours (on high setting the last 2 to 4 hours).
Fruit should cook until almost an applesauce capacity.
You can use a potato masher to get rid of lumps.
For each pint of cooked fruit, add sugar, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on high setting for 6 to 8 hours, stirring about every 2 hours.
Remove cover after 3 hours to allow fruit and juice to cook down.
Spoon into hot jars and process in boiling water bath. Makes about 5 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: garlic roasted mashed potatoes
directions: Place garlic on a square of aluminum foil; drizzle with oil, and wrap in foil.
Bake at 425 degrees for 30 min; remove from oven, and set aside.
Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 15-20 min. or until tender; drain and transfer to a large mixing bowl. Add butter and remaining ingredients; beat at medium speed until fluffy.
Cut off pointed ends of garlic; squeeze pulp from garlic cloves, and stir into mashed potatoes.
Serves 8. Very good!

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix ingredients and leave uncovered on kitchen counter for 3 days, stirring occasionally.
Place mixture in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days and feed with the following at least twice before using starter to bake bread.

title: vidalia onion pickles
directions: Slice onions; add salt and cover with ice and water.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over onions and heat just to boil.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: molasses crinkle cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, egg and molasses.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoon into balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake until set at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Watch carefully.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: mama shari's chicken-n-rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 13 x 9-inch glass pan stir first 5 ingredients.
Arrange chicken on top and brush with melted butter. Sprinkle chicken with chicken seasoning and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until chicken is lightly brown.

title: pasta chicken salad
directions: In small nonstick skillet, stir sesame seed over medium heat until golden brown.
In a large bowl, combine pasta, chicken, bell pepper, green onion, carrot and sesame seed.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Chop all vegetables.
Add all ingredients to spaghetti.
Serve cold.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cream; bring to boil on stove until mixture forms soft ball stage in cold water.
Take off stove and stir in peanut butter.
Stir until candy is hard.
Pour out into platter and cut into squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large bowl, mash bananas.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add melted and cooled butter.
Blend well.
Add sugar.
Stir in flour. Blend well.
Add nuts.
Mix well; pour in 3 (8 x 4-inch) pans, greased and lightly floured.
Add mixture.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Allow to cool.
Turn each bread onto foil; wrap.
Keep refrigerated until used.

title: pink and pretty pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple.
Chill to unbeaten egg white consistency.
Stir in sour cream, nuts and cherries.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Chill to firm.
Cut in squares.
Serves 8.

title: mexican orange candy(christmas candy)
directions: Caramelize the 1 cup sugar by sifting slowly into a hot frying pan.
Stir	to
prevent burning.
Add boiling water and boil until sugar
is
dissolved.
Add	2
cups sugar, milk and salt and boil to	soft
ball stage, stirring constantly.	Add orange rind (remove
from
heat)
and
beat until it thickens. Add nuts and put
in greased baking pan or dish.
Cut in small squares when solid.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil sausage 10 minutes.
Add zucchini until heated through. Pour 1/2 cup sauce into casserole dish; add drained sausage and zucchini.
Add balance of sauce on top.
Bake at 350° until zucchini is tender.
Add Mozzarella cheese if desired.
Return to oven an additional 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: grilled shrimp kabobs
directions: You will need 1 package of skewers.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
Then peel and mash.
Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls.
Roll balls into flour. Drop into boiling water and cook about 10 to 15 minutes or until they float to the top.

title: sausage balls
directions: Work all together.
Make into balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Can be wrapped around stuffed olives.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop corn.
In pan, combine all other ingredients, except soda and popcorn.
Bring to boil.
Continue to boil for 2 minutes. Stir in baking soda.
Put popped corn in brown paper bag.
Pour syrup over corn; shake gently.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High. Shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes more.
Pour onto flat pan to cool. Mixture will be very hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in hot water and mix with dressing.
Put one-third of this mixture in the bottom of a baking dish.
Add a layer
of
chicken.
Combine
soups
and
1 can of water or broth. Pour
over
the
layers
in
dish.
Top with remaining dressing. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook salt pork; drain.
Reserve liquid.
Combine onions, celery, scallions, olive oil and butter.
Cook until onions are translucent.
Add potatoes and clams with their juice.
Cover with water.
Cook potatoes.
Add cream and milk and garnish with parsley and salt pork.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage; drain off grease.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dishes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 (13 x 9-inch) dishes.

title: thai fried rice
directions: Melt margarine; add 2 thin slices of ginger root and stir 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove ginger root.
Add meat, onions (white part sliced thin, green part 1-inch long).
If fresh meat is used, cook until meat loses red color (1 to 2 minutes).
Add rice and m.s.g. Stir-fry for another 1 to 2 minutes.
Break an egg over mixture and stir in.
Cook about 1 more minute, stirring constantly. Serve with soy sauce.
Very good with sliced tomatoes and cucumbers.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, melted butter, nuts and sugar.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese with 1/4 cup of sugar and the milk.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture over cool crust.
Make lemon instant pudding according to directions.
Top over cream cheese mixture.
Chill, then spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Decorate with nuts (if desired).

title: cincinnati chili
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook beef, green pepper, onion, chili powder and garlic until beef is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat. Add soup, undrained kidney beans, vinegar and cinnamon.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over spaghetti. Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Cover each piece with mixture of cinnamon and sugar; cover completely.
Place 1/2 in Bundt pan. Melt butter; pour over bottom half.
Add rest, pour rest of butter over top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Set 5 minutes and flip pan.

title: quick rice dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in microwave for 30 minutes.
Stir and cook approximately 10 more minutes or until rice is tender.

title: zesty lima beans
directions: Combine beans and water in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave at High for 5 minutes. Reduce heat to Medium-high (70% power); cover and microwave for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender, stirring every 5 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes; drain.
Add celery and remaining ingredients to beans.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 1 minute or until thoroughly heated.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Yields 4 servings.

title: aunt pitty pat's pound cake
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating until smooth.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; add to sugar mixture alternately with sour cream and whiskey, beginning and ending with flour.

title: spicy pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until mixture is thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, walnuts and currants until thoroughly blended.
Stir gently into zucchini mixture just until blended.
Spoon batter equally into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread begins to pull away from sides of pan.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake(makes one 9-inch cheesecake)
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust, set aside. In heavy saucepan over very low heat, melt chips, stirring constantly.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add melted chips and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until center is set. Cool; chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add to shortening mixture.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned but still soft (8 to 10 minutes).
Makes 5 dozen.

title: rhubarb casserole
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Serve hot.

title: heidi's apple cake
directions: Stir together flour, wheat germ, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg; set aside.
In large bowl, combine apples, sugars, oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gently.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool. Cut in squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in half.
Place on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer strawberries on top of Twinkies.
Next, spread crushed pineapple.
Layer sliced bananas.
Mix pudding according to directions and spread.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Beat eggs 1 minute or until light.
Cream shortening; continue beating while adding sugars.
Then beat until thoroughly mixed. Add beaten eggs.
Mix until blended.
Add half of dry ingredients and beat about 1 minute.
Ad the rest of the dry ingredients and nuts.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Divide dough into two parts.
Roll each in wax paper.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Slice about 1/8-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 40 to 45 cookies.
Ice if desired.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate several hours.
Keeps well.

title: my favorite cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes

title: campfire stew
directions: Cook meat until well done and drain.
Add soup and Veg-All. Simmer.
Serve over mashed potatoes, rice or egg noodles.

title: dietetic cooler
directions: For each serving, pour pineapple juice and mint extract into a tall glass.
Stir to mix, then add low calorie ginger ale. Garnish with mint.

title: hamburger and corn casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic powder.
Let cook.
Mix: corn, 2 eggs, sugar, milk and corn mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frosted spice pecans
directions: Combine 1 egg white (beaten slightly with fork), water and sugar.
Add and blend salt, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Add pecan halves and stir until each nut is well coated.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake one hour or until golden brown in a 250° oven.

title: peach rum jam
directions: Combine peaches and pectin in a very large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Place over high heat and bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Immediately add all the sugar and stir. Again bring to a full rolling boil and boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut shortening in flour until it resembles coarse corn meal.
Combine beaten egg, vinegar and water and blend.
Add to flour mixture and stir until well mixed. Roll out on floured surface.
(This easily makes two 9-inch crusts.)

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use (will keep 3 to 4 days).
Spoon into well-greased muffin tins (dough will be thin).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs, then bananas.
Add to sugar mixture, alternate with dry ingredients.
Add chopped walnuts. Pour into a greased 9 x 5 loaf pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: frozen cheesecake
directions: Mix crackers, margarine and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch container.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and cool. Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, then add Jell-O.
Whip Milnot until stiff, then fold in Jell-O and cream cheese mixture. Pour over crust and freeze until needed.

title: quick minestrone soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add rest of ingredients using enough water to make soup consistency desired.
May be made in kettle on top of the stove or is a wonderful slow cooker recipe.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Melt margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup together over very low heat until sugar isn't grainy anymore.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, put in raw rice.
Cut butter over rice.
Spoon soup over rice.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over rice.
Cover with water.
Season chicken
and place chicken pieces on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325 degrees for 1-1/2 hours.

title: texas style potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the hash browns, corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Thaw the potatoes.
Add other mixed ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with the crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Toast bread.
Butter both sides and cut diagonally.
Mix ground beef, onion, celery, prepared mustard and 1/2 teaspoon salt in medium size frying pan.
Cook over medium heat until meat is lightly browned.
Arrange toast, cheese and hamburger mixture in alternate layers in greased 9-inch square pan, ending with cheese as top layer.
Mix egg, milk, dry mustard, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour over layers in pan. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Stir flour, baking powder, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa and salt together in large bowl.
Beat in milk, vanilla and oil until smooth.
Pour into greased 8-inch baking pan.
Mix brown sugar with 3 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over batter in pan.
Pour hot (not boiling) water over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: mexican hot bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 450° about 20 minutes or until well done.

title: hot five-bean salad
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Return reserved drippings to skillet.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Blend into drippings.
Stir until boiling.
Drain all beans.
Stir into skillet.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn into serving dish.
Crumble bacon over top.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix well, but do not beat.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat, onions, garlic and chili powder.
Simmer and cool. In a bowl, mix cornmeal, tomato sauce, corn, oil, olives and eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: microwave vegetable lasagna(a delicious recipe!  don't tell the kids it's full of veggies!)
directions: Remove paper from spinach box.
Place unopened box on paper towel lined plate.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Drain.

title: fresh garden dish(primavera)
directions: In skillet on medium heat, cook vegetables until tender.
Stir in tomatoes.
Toss vegetable mixture with noodles.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour, salt, vanilla and syrup.
Stir well.
Add pecans.
Bake 1/2 or 3/4 hour. Start oven at 375° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Pie is done when it is firm.
Do not overcook.

title: baked fish in lemon sauce
directions: In baking dish, put onion and green pepper on fish.
Pour sauce onto fish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: amazing apple salad
directions: Peel, core and cut apples into small chunks.
Peel and grate the carrots or make long, thin strips with a vegetable peeler. Chop the celery into small pieces.
Mix the carrots, celery and apples together with a fork.
Add the other ingredients and mix until well coated with mayonnaise or yogurt.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Pour sauerkraut, juice included, into a 3-quart saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add enough water to cover kraut and bring to a simmer.
Add sausage or ham while it is cooking.
Heat vegetable oil in skillet.
Add sliced onion.
Stir frequently, cooking slowly until onion is tender.
Add flour to onion.
Stir briskly until flour is thick.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and stir rapidly with whisk. Stir and cook for 2 minutes; add flour and onion to sauerkraut. Mix well and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Preheat the oven to moderate (350°).
Combine the soup, milk, vermouth and the Worcestershire sauce in a large saucepan; heat slowly, stirring often, until bubbly.
Fold in the seafood and rice.
Spoon into a 6-cup shallow casserole.
Bake in the preheated moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes or until bubbly hot. Spoon the cooked peas around the edge of the dish; garnish with twists of lemon, if you wish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange apricot nog
directions: In blender combine undrained apricots and rest of ingredients, except nutmeg.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into small glasses and sprinkle with nutmeg to taste.
Serve immediately. Serves 8 to 10.

title: pineapple pie - baked graham cracker crust
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice.
Stir well.
Fold in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: confetti peanut bars
directions: In Dutch oven, melt marshmallows with 3 tablespoons butter and peanut butter until smooth.
Add peanut butter chips; melt, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Add popcorn and peanuts; toss until well mixed.
Gently fold in candy coated chips until evenly distributed.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cool completely.
In microwave, melt chocolate chips with remaining butter; mix until smooth.
Drizzle chocolate evenly over top of popcorn.
Cool until hard; cut into 16 bars.

title: chili sauce (aunt frances)
directions: Cut vegetables coarse.
Mix in large pan.
Cook until very thick on a low heat.
Taste for spice balance.
Stir often.
Seal in tight jars.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and flavorings.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out on floured pastry sheet.
Cut out with cookie cutter in desired shape.
Dip cutter in flour after each cutting. Bake in lightly greased cookie sheet for 7 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Add shortening, half of mashed banana and eggs.
Mix to moisten flour.
Last, add remaining banana and vanilla.
Mix by hand until well blended.
You can also add chopped walnuts, if desired.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 370° for 30 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat ingredients for 2 minutes.
Bake in 9-inch pie plate (greased).
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: phillips favorite candy
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave oven, stirring every 30 seconds until smooth and creamy.
Stir in nuts until well coated.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let set until firm.

title: coconut drops
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop cookie dough by teaspoon 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: amish carrots
directions: Cut carrots on diagonal. Cook in salted water until tender. Drain; reserve 1/4 cup liquid. Mix onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and carrot liquid. Combine with carrots in a buttered casserole. Mix bread crumbs with melted butter. Spread over carrots. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 6.

title: meringue
directions: Add water to your egg whites, then beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly beat sugar and cream of tartar into egg whites. Brown in oven.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Layer hash browns, soup and sour cream mixture, onion, cheese, corn flakes and butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put lemon, orange, spices and honey in the coffeepot basket, then pour the cider over it; let it perk.

title: chocolate peanut butter brickle
directions: Spread saltines over foil-lined cookie sheet so that cookie sheet is completely covered.
Mix margarine and sugar.
Boil for no more than 2 minutes.
Spread over saltines and bake for 7 minutes at 400°.
Then pour 1 bag of each chocolate morsels and peanut butter morsels over the hot saltines.
Spread out as the morsels melt.
Refrigerate.
Bake apart when completely cooled.

title: southern spoon bread(from boone tavern, berea, kentucky)
directions: Stir meal into rapidly boiling milk.
Cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
Allow to cool.
Add well beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Beat in mixer 15 minutes.
Pour into well-greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve from casserole with spoon.

title: nacho with salsa
directions: Spread tortilla chips
one
layer deep in shallow baking dish. Sprinkle tortillas
with
cheese
and
dot
with desired amount of salsa.
Place in
350° oven for 4 to 6 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: cheddar apple pie
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, half cup flour and cheese and set aside.
Gently combine remaining ingredients; heap into an unbaked pastry shell.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: oatmeal-wheat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, shortening, egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, but not hard; 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil the oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Sift together sugar and flour.
Pour liquid over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit fantasy
directions: Mix pudding and juice from fruit cocktail; add in Cool Whip and drained fruits.
Chill for 30 minutes; mix and serve.

title: red sherbet smash
directions: In punch bowl, combine red punch mix, lemonade concentrate and water; stir to dissolve.
Chill before serving.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown pork chops.
Spread rice over the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Reserve 2 teaspoons onion soup mix and sprinkle the rest over the rice.
Reserve mushroom liquid and spread mushrooms over the rice.
Add pimentos.
Add enough water to mushroom liquid to total 3 cups.
Pour over rice mixture. Place pork chops on top of rice, then sprinkle with remaining soup mix. Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on thickness of pork chops.

title: dark chocolate glaze
directions: Melt
chocolate
in
small saucepan over very low heat. Add butter and water and stir until smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in confectioners sugar and beat with wire whisk, spoon or electric mixer until smooth.
Pour frosting on cake, allowing it to drip naturally, to make a thick, shiny glaze.

title: creamy thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until smooth.
Cover; chill. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box and rinse with cold water. Add chopped cucumbers and onions, vinegar, sugar and Marzetti slaw dressing.
Mix well.
Make day before used.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix rice (uncooked), broth and soups into a baking dish. Place cut-up chicken over the mixture.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: sunny silver pie
directions: Beat the 6 egg yolks.
Add 3/4 cup white sugar, 5 tablespoons lemon juice and grated rind of 1 lemon.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Turn off heat and add 1 1/2 teaspoons of gelatin soaked in 3/4 glass of water.
Leave set until almost cool.
Beat egg whites; add 3/4 cup sugar.
Add cooked ingredients to egg whites and pour into pie crusts.
Place in refrigerator until firm. Top with whipped cream.
This makes three 9-inch pies.

title: turkey chili
directions: In a nonstick pan over high heat, brown turkey meat.

Onion and green pepper may be added at this time, if desired. Add V-8 juice, Chili-O mix and water, stirring well. Reduce heat and add the tomatoes, chili powder, salt and pepper. Stir well and cook 10 minutes on low heat, covered. Add chili beans and cook another 10 minutes. Serve alone or over noodles.

title: swedish lemon rings
directions: Start heating oven to 400°.
Sift flour, 3/4 cup of the sugar and salt into large mixing bowl.
Add lemon juice.
Cut in butter with pastry blender; mix with spoon to smooth dough.
Flour hands and pinch off pieces of dough.
Roll into pencil-thick strips 3-inches long.
Twist two strips together; shape into ring.
Mix almonds and remaining sugar on waxed paper.
Press rings into mixture; place almond side up on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 8 minutes.
Do not brown.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix 1/2 sugar with cracker crumbs and nuts.
Mix 1/2 sugar with vanilla and egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Combine mixtures. Place in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs with fork. Add milk, sugar, vanilla and salt. Blend. Stir in rice and raisins. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 1 hour and 15 minutes, stirring once. Sprinkle brown sugar on top just before serving and broil 2 to 3 minutes about 5-inches until sugar melts.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and buttermilk.
Then add bananas, nuts and flavoring.
Bake at 375° in a loaf pan for 40 to 45 minutes or a 9 x 13-inch pan for 60 to 65 minutes, when doubling the recipe.

title: potato chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Melt margarine, then mix all liquid ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350°.

title: caesar salad
directions: Cut up lettuce in large salad bowl.
Make hole in center and drop crisp croutons (made beforehand by deep-frying cubes of French bread until browned).
Sprinkle salt and pepper over top. Pour garlic oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, chopped anchovies and coddled egg over top.
While thoroughly mixing sprinkle Parmesan cheese generously through.
Serve immediately.

title: chow-chow pickle relish
directions: Tomatoes, peppers, onions and cabbage may be put through coarse chopper. Add salt. Cover with cold water and let stand overnight. Drain. Add remaining ingredients. Cook to boiling point and simmer slowly 15 minutes. Makes 4 pints.

title: bee's lemon jelly filling
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Meanwhile, beat egg yolks well.
Add sugar, salt and flour.
Add hot water and lemon juice, then stir into melted butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring all the time.
Use as filling and/or icing for white cake.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 cup margarine in small saucepan. Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, then water. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture and beat well.
Stir in 1/3 cup condensed milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake 15 minutes or until springs back when lightly touched.

title: green chilie chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat soup and green chilies in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Dip 3 tortillas in mixture and place in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Top with third of chicken, onion and cheese. Repeat, making 3 more layers, ending with cheese. Pour remaining soup with chilies and sour cream over casserole. Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and hot.

title: simple stroganoff
directions: Cook ground beef with onion.
Add beef broth, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Cover; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Add noodles and sour cream.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in oil, zucchini, sugar and vanilla. Sift four, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt onto waxed paper.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Put into well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: tuna treet
directions: Mix ingredients together and heat over full flame in covered skillet.
When it comes to a boil, turn flame to a simmer and cook for 10 minutes.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Cream together lard, oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Pour into a tube pan.
Start off cooking in a cold oven and cook at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: prize cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine shortening and sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add to wet and mix well.
Crumble mincemeat into mixture and stir. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
If desired, glaze with zigzags of powdered sugar icing.

title: johnny cake(small)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: beef ring with candied carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Mix lightly; add only enough water to make mixture workable.
Pat gently into a 6-cup ring mold, then invert on a rack in a baking pan.
Remove ring mold.
Or, shape meat loaf by hand into a big doughnut. Sprinkle top with crumbs, then bake in a moderate oven at 325° for 1 hour. Remove to a platter and fill center with candied carrots.

title: irish bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda in large bowl; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten egg; blend.
Add buttermilk; blend well.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients and mix (by hand) together until dry ingredients are well moistened.
Add caraway seeds and mix.
Fold in raisins until completely dispersed into mixture.
Grease 1 1/2-quart glass casserole or 1 loaf bread tin.
Pour in mixture. Brush top with melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake about another 30 minutes.
Test middle of bread with toothpick to make sure it's fully cooked.

title: ham stuffed celery
directions: Combine ham, lemon juice, pecans and cheese.
Mix well.
Fill celery stalks with mixture and chill before serving.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Heat shortening in skillet.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into skillet and fry on both sides until brown.

title: anise biscotte
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Sift flour and add baking powder; work in butter.
Combine egg and sugar mixture to flour and knead 5 to 10 minutes until smooth.
Roll into loaves.
Brush with egg glaze. Bake for 15 minutes in moderate oven at 375° to 400°.
Cool very slightly; slice, rebake until golden brown.
Cookie is hard.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute onions; add peppers, eggplant and zucchini and cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except lemon juice.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, then sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix everything together in large dish pan for cooker.
Boil until vegetables change light color.
Pour into pint jars and seal immediately.

title: baked apples with sauce
directions: Wash and core the apples.
Fill the center with sugar and cinnamon.
Pour a little water over the apples.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spicy breaded chicken for diabetics
directions: In a plastic bag, mix bread crumbs, powdered milk, chili powder, garlic powder and dry mustard; set aside.
Place milk in shallow pan. Dip chicken pieces into milk, then place in bag and shake to coat.
Place chicken, bone side down, in a 13 x 9-inch pan coated with vegetable spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: bama chili
directions: Open cans and pour contents in 6 quart crock-pot.
Stir in seasoning packets.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Season with onion, salt, lemon pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain browned ground beef and stir into crock-pot mixture.
Cook 3 hours, then refrigerate overnight for spices to ripen.

title: kahlua brownies
directions: Resift flour with baking powder and salt. Melt butter with chocolate over very low heat or over hot water. Beat eggs with sugar until light. Stir in chocolate mixture and 1/4 cup Kahlua. Add flour mixture and mix well; stir in walnuts. Turn into greased 9-inch square pan, bottom-lined with greased parchment or foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until top springs back. Be careful not to over bake. When cool, brush top with 1 tablespoon Kahlua. Cut into bars.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix together
and
spread
in 10 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and saute onions and pepper until golden brown in bacon fat.
Add next 4 ingredients and place in 1 1/4-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Stir in coconut.
Drop rounded teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Cook bacon and crumble it into small pieces.
In saucepan over low heat, melt Velveeta.
Combine cheese, mayonnaise and potatoes in large bowl and mix well.
Use shallow baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake uncovered for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hobo potatoes
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine potatoes, onions, celery, carrots and water.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Grease (or use Pam) a 10-inch baking dish.
Line with potatoes.
Heat soup and water in small pan until smooth; stir frequently.
Add sausage; pour over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, covered.
Remove lid and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: ice cream cone
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add oil and egg whites; mix until smooth.
Add water and vanilla.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine baking soda, water and vanilla in a small dish and set aside.
Place sugar, water and corn syrup in a deep 3-quart heat resistant, non-metallic casserole.
Stir to blend.
Heat, uncovered, on Full power 12 minutes or until candy thermometer registers 240° (soft ball stage).
Stir in butter until melted. Add peanuts and heat, uncovered, on Full power 20 minutes or until candy thermometer registers 300° (hard crack).
Grease 2 cookie sheets and warm in a conventional oven at 250° while peanut mixture is heating.
Stir reserved baking soda mixture into hot candy mixture.
Pour hot peanut brittle onto prepared cookie sheets and spread to 1/4-inch thickness.
When peanut brittle has cooled, break into bite-size pieces.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, stir soup and soy sauce until smooth. Mix in 1/2 can onions, beans and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Bring to a boil, sugar, chocolate, butter and milk.
Take off heat, then add vanilla, then add oats, coconut and nuts.
Stir up real good, then spoon out by two teaspoons on wax paper until cool.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt the butter or margarine in the pan that you are going to use.
Mix the remaining ingredients together, except peaches. Pour batter in pan with butter.
Pour drained peaches on batter. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine milk, 1/2 cup melted butter, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Heat until butter is melted.
Cool to 105° to 115°. Stir in yeast until dissolved.
Place flour in a large bowl; make a well in the flour and pour in the liquid mixture.
Stir until blended.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Turn dough out on a floured surface and roll to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in 3-inch squares.
Dip each square into the remaining butter and layer squares in a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Let rise until doubled in bulk, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sugar-free date nut cake
directions: Cream margarine, sweetener, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking soda and spices; mix well. Fold in dates, applesauce and nuts. Pour into greased tube pan or loaf pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done in center.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs and juice from oranges.
Add oranges and nuts.
Pour into pan and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: german chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Spread about 2/3 of the dough (will be stiff) into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook for 6 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until served.
Serve with crackers or bread chunks.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Make pudding following directions on box.
Add cream cheese mixture and Cool Whip to pudding.
Mix together.
Add crushed pineapple (do not drain).
Break angel food cake into small pieces and mix into pudding mixture.

title: corn soup
directions: Cook pepper and onion in oil and margarine until tender.
Stir in the flour.
Stir over low heat for a few minutes.
Add milk slowly and stir frequently to avoid lumping.
Set aside.
Place 1 cup corn and cream in blender.
Blend until somewhat smooth.
Add corn and cream mixture and remaining corn to the milk mixture. Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer slowly until thoroughly heated. May be garnished with parsley.

title: green and white salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O with water and juice.
Cool, add pineapple.
Pour into deep dish, chill until firm.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in water and juice; let cool.
Soften cream cheese and add to lemon mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour lemon Jell-O mixture over lime Jell-O mixture.
Return to refrigerator and chill until firm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add liquid from mushrooms and the seasonings.
Add soup gradually, stirring until smooth.
Add milk, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Mix chicken, spaghetti, mushrooms and pimentos.
Add the sauce.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: celery salmon loaf
directions: For sauce, heat cream of celery soup mixed with 1/2 cup milk and parsley.

title: easy macaroni and cheese(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Cut 10 slices cheese food into pieces.
In saucepan, melt margarine; stir in flour, bouillon and mustard.
Gradually add milk; cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat. Add cheese food pieces; stir until melted.
Add macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with remaining cheese food slices.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: zesty italian crescent casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. In large skillet, brown beef and onion until beef is thoroughly cooked. Drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce, heating thoroughly. In medium bowl, mix mozzarella cheese and sour cream. Pour hot meat mixture into ungreased 12 x 8 baking dish. Spoon cheese mixture over meat. Unroll dough over cheese mixture. In another small bowl, combine butter and parmesan cheese. Spread evenly over dough. Bake at 375 degrees for 18-25 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with green salad and garlic bread.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; beat well. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and then add vanilla. Drop by large teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fillet of sole in lemon parsley butter
directions: Place margarine in rectangular baking dish, 12 x 8-inch, or 10-inch square casserole.
Microwave at High (100%) until melted, 45 seconds to 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Blend in remaining ingredients except fish fillets.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine crust ingredients; press into a 9 inch pie plate. Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Stir in
milk.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and corn meal.
Add to milk mixture.
Stir to mix, then add oil and stir well.
Pour in greased and floured pan and bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over butter.
Press down.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Sprinkle chocolate bits, then butterscotch bits. Pour milk evenly over all.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Press lightly. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 48.

title: heavenly delight salad
directions: Boil eggs, water and vinegar until thick.
Cool.
Pour over marshmallows and diced fruit.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill overnight.

title: popovers
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl. Make a well in center of flour. Add eggs, butter and milk. Beat until smooth. Fill a well greased 5 oz. Custard Cups or Muffin pan 1\2 full.
Bake at 400° for 35-40 min, until brown and crisp.

title: ice cream topping(butterscotch)
directions: Cook together 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Store in a cool place.
Tastes like the store bought kind.

title: rubies in the dirt
directions: Layer each ingredient.
Top with crown of unsweetened berries. Before layering, tear chocolate cake into pieces.
Chill layered mixture at least 4 hours.
Serve with spoon.

title: ree's jerky
directions: Cut the venison or beef into thin strips.
Dip into the mixture.
Then put into dryer or dehydrator.
Dry until it's the way you like it.

title: broiler chicken parmesan
directions: In a medium sized bowl, combine the hot water, butter, vinegar, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Stir until butter is melted.
Arrange the chicken on a broiler pan side by side.
With a basting brush, coat the top of each chicken piece.

title: baked potatoes florentine
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, bake potatoes 50 to 60 minutes in 450° oven.
Meanwhile, cook spinach as directed on label; drain.
When potatoes are fork tender, cut lengthwise in half and scoop out pulp.
With electric mixer, at medium speed, combine potato pulp, egg yolks, salt, pepper, onion powder and nutmeg.
Beat until very smooth.
Stir in drained spinach.
Heap potato mixture back into shells.
Cut cheese into eight strips, placing 1 on each potato.
Place on cookie sheet and return to 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and potatoes are hot!

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, eggs, parsley, onion, salt and 1/4 cup tomato soup. Mix together; shape into meatballs. Place in skillet. Mix soup, water and sauce. Pour over meatballs.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Simmer 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy(a breakfast treat)
directions: Add flour, cocoa, sugar, milk and vanilla in skillet with grease.
Cook on medium heat (flame) until gravy thickens, stirring constantly.
Serve with hot biscuits and butter.

title: corn souffle
directions: Beat eggs. Add sour cream and mix.
Add butter, corn, muffin mix and salt.
Mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cornmeal. Add lemon juice, grated rind, milk and melted shortening. Add eggs one at a time. Eggs should be room temperature. Carefully pour into pie shell and bake in pre-heated 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter in 2-quart casserole dish at 350°. Mix sugar, flour and milk. Add to butter. Add peaches last. Do not stir. Cook for 1 hour.

title: hamburger corn pone
directions: Brown onion and meat in small amount of shortening.
Add beans, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Pour into greased baking dish and top with thin cornbread batter.
Bake about 30 minutes in 400° oven.
Serve hot.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 bread tins.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except dry.
Mix by hand well, then add the dry ingredients and last the coconut, chopped dates, chopped nuts and cut orange pieces.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
In smaller pans, bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: plum nut bread
directions: Prepare plums.
Cream butter or oleo with sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Blend yogurt and lemon peel and add to creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Add chopped nuts and chopped plums; mix well.
Divide between 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans . Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs. Add butter, baking powder and salt.
Add flour and mix. Roll out and cut into strips. Cook in chicken or beef broth until done by taste.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, garlic and seasonings.
Toss gently with mushrooms and onion.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours.
Drain before serving.
Excellent as an appetizer.
Great for picnics.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Simmer the first 6 ingredients.
Add meat, cheese and rice. Put into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts. Makes 4 servings (1 vegetable, 3 proteins, 1 bread and 2 1/2 optional calories).

title: quick meat pie
directions: Cut meat in small pieces.
Cook potatoes in meat and broth. Put in baking dish or pan.
Make dough with the remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on potatoes and meat mixture; bake until brown.

title: tom fina's holiday egg nog
directions: Separate eggs.
In a large mixing bowl, whip egg whites until they are stiff and dry.
Gently fold sugar in.
Whip yolks until they are thick.
Fold the thickened yolks into egg whites.
With the mixer, on slow speed, gradually add milk, cream and alcohol (if desired).
Makes two quarts.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies(makes 8 to 9 dozen)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until creamy, Add vanilla, Beat well. Combine remaining ingredients, mix well.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix with enough half and half to make a paste.
Add melted butter.
Beat the egg yolks and 1 whole egg.
Add beaten eggs and rest of the half and half and cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cover and cool.
When filling has cooled, turn into a baked pie crust.
Top with Superior Meringue.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Let pie cool and sprinkle with 4 ounces grated semi-sweet chocolate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix next 2 ingredients and sprinkle over top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: orange carrots
directions: Slice carrots into rounds or sticks.
Add carrots to boiling salted water.
Cover and cook until tender; drain.
Add orange pieces, rind, margarine and syrup.
Place over low heat.
Stir gently until margarine is melted and orange is heated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar and rhubarb.
(A little red food coloring may be added.)
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 1 cup sugar, flour and soda.
Cut in margarine.
Stir in coconut, vanilla and walnuts.
Spread over top of rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until rhubarb is tender and topping is brown.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Blend together until dough forms.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brush with water.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: raisin black walnut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and butter.
Beat until fluffy; add syrup and beat again until fluffy.
Add nuts and vanilla and beat; add raisins and beat gently.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 375°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with 1/2 of the Doritos.
Mix all other ingredients, saving 1/2 the cheese.
Pour meat mix over Doritos.
Add another layer of Doritos and put rest of cheese on top.
If you like it hot, add chopped green chilies on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: white frosting for coconut cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Pour the boiling water over ingredients.
Beat at high speed.
When mixture starts to peak, add vanilla and continue beating until completely peaked. Spread over cake and sprinkle coconut.

title: canadian style seafood casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 3 tablespoons butter; add salt and pepper.
Bring milk to a boil and mix in 1/2 cup butter and flour; add celery and onion, then cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted and sauce has thickened.
Add seafood; place in one large or several individual casseroles.
Heat until bubbling in 350° oven.
Serve over rice.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
(Pan should be 1/2 to 3/4 full.)
Blend butter, sugar and flour until crumbly. Scatter over apples and pat down.
Two tablespoons water should be sprinkled over apples first.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Can be served plain or with whipped cream, milk or ice cream.
Good cold.

title: cheese garlic bread
directions: Combine the Bisquick mix, cheese and milk to form a stiff dough. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
While biscuits bake, combine the melted margarine and garlic powder. Brush over warm biscuits before removing from pan.

title: favorite casserole(goes with any entree)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients; cover and bake 1 hour.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix well; refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 350° to 400°, uncovered.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage to loosen the leaves. Mix all ingredients together except bacon and tomatoes. Put about 4 tablespoons of mixture on cabbage leaf and roll up. Place in Dutch oven. Fill Dutch oven with cabbage rolls. Place bacon strips on top. Pour in 2 cans of water. Cover and cook over moderate heat for 30 minutes. Then put can of tomatoes over rolls and cook about 30 minutes more. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Brown chops on both
sides
in hot oil in a heavy skillet. top with
sauerkraut, caraway seed and tomato.
Sprinkle with paprika; cover and
simmer
40 minutes or until chops are tender. Yield:
4 servings.

title: fri-chick tater tot bake
directions: Note: To shorten cooking time, microwave Tater Tots for 6 minutes before layering in baking dish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 2 (4 x 8-inch) pans.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Break eggs and beat well.
Beat in vanilla, oil, and sugar.
Stir in zucchini. Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt.
Stir in thoroughly.
Add nuts and/or pineapple, if desired.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: opakapaka mediterranean
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook and stir onions and peppers in oil in large skillet on medium-high for 5 minutes or until tender, but crisp.
Add tomatoes and garlic; mix lightly.

title: potato casserole deluxe
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix last 2 ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: clam spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in ovenproof dish. Pour melted butter on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: mary's swedish pineapple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Mix ingredients well. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: pecan tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Stir until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into thawed pie shell.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: pickled vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables well.
Then mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and water together; pour over vegetables.
Let stand 48 hours before serving.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove bones and skin and flake.
Mix cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke. Add salmon.
Form into ball and chill at least 4 hours.
Lightly press nuts and parsley on salmon ball to garnish.

title: pickled squash
directions: Salt squash, onion, peppers and carrots and let stand for 1 hour.
Bring to a boil sugar, vinegar, celery seed and allspice. Drain vegetables and pack into jars.
Pour hot syrup over them. Seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute mushrooms, garlic and onion.
Remove.
Cook meat until light brown.
Reserving 1/3 cup of broth, stir in remaining broth with meat.
Add ketchup and salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes with reserved broth; add 3 tablespoons flour and pour into meat mixture.
Add mushrooms, garlic and onion.
Heat to boil; boil one minute to thicken sauce.
Reduce heat.
Add sour cream and heat.
Pour over noodles.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop each pack of beef separately.
Chop tops of green onions. Soften both packs of cream cheese.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put the cooked macaroni into the dish, pour the cheese sauce over it and mix gently with a fork.
Sprinkle the grated cheese evenly over the top and spread the crumbs over the cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until the top is golden and the sauce is bubbling, about 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand a day or more.
The flavor gets better the longer it stands.
Use the pudding mix dry just as it comes from the package.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortilla shells.
Spread mixture on shells and slice.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over chicken and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lo-cal garlic dip
directions: Beat cottage cheese with milk until smooth.
Add garlic salt. Chill, covered, for 10 to 12 hours.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Bone chicken breasts, remove skin and cut each breast half into 6 to 8 nuggets, about 1 1/2-inches square.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, Accent, salt and herbs.
Dip chicken nuggets in melted butter, then crumb mixture.
Place in single layer on foil-lined baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put in greased and meal dusted pan, 1/2 of the mixture and 1/2 of the cheese.
Add remaining mixture and spread balance of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon-lime chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow glass dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Drain, discarding marinade.
Grill chicken over medium-hot coals, turning once, until juices run clear, about 15-18 minutes.

title: blueberry fluff
directions: Crust:
Combine the oleo and graham cracker crumbs; mix.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 4 hours.
Add cookies right before serving.

title: beefy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix beef, horseradish, chives or onion, garlic salt and pepper together in a bowl.
Remove stems from mushrooms (sometimes I finely chop the stems and add to meat mixture).
Stuff mushrooms with beef mixture.
Place in a shallow baking dish; pour wine over mushrooms.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, until beef is done.
Makes 18 appetizers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers; sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour over ice.
Add onions to cucumbers. Let spices and vinegar boil; add cucumber mixture.
Cook until tender.
Process 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter-cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust.
Chill 5 to 6 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
This pie freezes well.

title: fruit and yogurt shake
directions: In a blender, combine undrained peaches, banana, yogurt and vanilla.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes and blend until frothy.
Makes 1 1/4 cups (2 servings).
One serving = 1 fruit exchange and 1/2 milk exchange.

title: antipasto pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package instructions; drain and rinse well with cold water.
In large bowl, toss cooled pasta with remaining ingredients until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate. Serve.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: popovers(light and tasty)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Grease 8 custard cups. In a small bowl, combine eggs, milk and butter. In another bowl, stir flour and salt together. Make a hole in flour mixture and add egg mixture, stirring just until lumps disappear. Fill custard cups 1/2 full. Bake for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake another 20 minutes. When popovers are done, remove immediately from pan so steam doesn't soften them. Serve hot with butter (and maybe honey?).

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together over low heat, then let cool.
Mix whipped cream and marshmallow mixture.
Fold in Hershey bars.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: squash and pepper cornbread
