directions: Shred the squash, pepper and onion.
Add the sausage.
Make a mixture of cornbread mix, 1 egg, salt, black pepper, Wesson oil, 1/2 cup flour and milk.
Add to vegetables.
Bake in muffin tins at 425° until golden brown.

title: cranberry sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, with mixer at medium speed.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together alternately with sour cream.
Start with dry and end with dry.
Add almond flavoring.
Grease an 8-inch tube pan.
Put 1/3 batter in pan, then swirl 1/3 of cranberry sauce.
Add another 1/3 batter; swirl 1/3 sauce and so on.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix first and third ingredients in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and cover and refrigerate.
Roll out biscuits or pinch off and use as needed or desired.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: marshmallow tarts
directions: Grease a muffin pan.
Slice cookie dough in 1/4-inch slices. Place in bottom of prepared muffin cups.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon coconut in each.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Cool; remove from pan.
Fill each tart with 2 teaspoons Marshmallow Creme.
Top with coconut, chopped nuts and chocolate chips.

title: seashell - broccoli salad
directions: Cook seashells as directed on the box.
Then drain.
In frying pan, cook bacon until crisp and drain.
Then place crumbled bacon in deep saucepan.
Add margarine and garlic and the box of chopped broccoli.
Saute 7 to 8 minutes.
To this mixture, add light whipping cream and Parmesan cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted. Add the cooked seashells and mix well.
Keep warm until ready to serve.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a bowl, mix Rotel tomatoes, cheddar cheese soup, cream of mushroom soup, water, onions. Salt and pepper to taste. Pour mixture over potatoes in a greased baking dish. Place margarine slices on top and bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are soft when stuck with fork.

title: mom's fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and melted butter.
Beat until creamy.
Add whole eggs, flour, salt, cocoa and vanilla.
Beat well!! Stir in pecans. Bake in a greased 8-inch pie pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 300°. Serve with whip cream or ice cream.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water until completely cool.
In large bowl, combine tomatoes, broccoli (which has been cooked 5 minutes), peas, dressing and basil.
Add cheeses and macaroni; toss lightly and chill.
Serves 10.

title: chuck roast cooked in foil
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper.
Place on heavy-duty foil in baking pan.
Sprinkle with dry soup mix and mushroom soup on top.
Seal foil tightly and bake at 325° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: onion dill bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add butter, sugar and salt; let cool.
Mix yeast and warm water.
Add milk mixture.
Add flour and herbs.
Knead mixture.
Let rise for approximately 1 hour.
Punch, knead and let rise another 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into buttered quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 50 minutes or until knife placed in center comes out clean.

title: white bean chili
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in undrained beans, undrained turkey beef, chili peppers, instant bouillon granules and chili powder and bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Ladle soup mixture into bowls.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.
Makes 3 servings.

title: nameless cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Blend in eggs, sifted flour, baking powder, soda, spices, salt, and cocoa. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Blend in vanilla and nuts. Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Frost with Mocha frosting.

title: spinach quiche
directions: I use low-fat cottage cheese, skim milk and add 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: biscuits(makes 6 pans)
directions: Melt lard and margarine.
Set aside.
Do not let get too hot. Combine flour and baking powder together.
Add milk.
Mix well. Add lard and margarine and stir until lard is mixed well and cannot be seen.
Knead entire mixture with flour and pat out.
Cut out with small water glass, 8 to a pan.
With pastry brush, coat pan and top with shortening.
Can be frozen and baked later.

title: quick cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pie filling, thoroughly. Put 3/4 dough in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over dough and top with remaining dough.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven. Cut in slices when cool.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick butter and 1 egg together; press into bottom of well greased pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup of pecans into crust.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, slice and boil until tender. Drain water.
Mash and add ingredients, leaving 1/2 cup cheese for topping.
Mix thoroughly and place into greased pan. Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: homemade noodles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add flour and salt.
Make a well in the flour.
Add your eggs in the center of the well and beat with a fork.
Pour milk into the mixture, stirring as you pour.
You need just enough milk to make mixture sticky.
Form into a ball. Tear the ball in half.
Flour the surface you are going to roll the mixture out on.
Roll out adding flour to keep the dough from sticking to the rolling pin.
When about 1/8-inch thick, cut with noodle cutter or use a knife.
Once the noodles are cut, put flour in your hands and toss with noodles.
Place on a cookie sheet to dry while you roll out the remaining dough.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water, then add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Stir until all dissolved thoroughly.
Chill until firm.
Is best to make this part the night before and put the topping on the next day.

title: oatmeal crunch bars
directions: Cream
butter with brown sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Press into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake
at
for
to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool;
cut
into bars.
For frosting, sprinkle 1/2
cup chocolate
pieces on hot bars.
When soft, spread to frost.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in rectangular dish or casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers in butter.
Add mushroom soup and stir.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and stir.
Cook for 20 minutes on medium heat.
Add crawfish and cook for 15 minutes on medium heat.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli, cut into bite-size pieces.
Chop boiled eggs and water chestnuts.
Add to broccoli along with onions and olives, toss with enough Ranch dressing to coat well. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour into corn mix.
Combine all other items; mix well.
Bake in a casserole dish for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, celery and carrots.
Cover with water; boil until tender.
Add milk and onion flakes.
Stir in noodles.
Stir constantly until noodles are tender.
Add butter (margarine) on top of heating soup.
Total cooking time from start to finish:
40 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken, vegetables and soups in a bowl.
Transfer to a greased 9-inch square pan.

title: herbed cream cheese
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients until well blended.
Chill overnight before serving for best taste. Serve with assorted crackers and party breads, pita or pretzel chips.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve with Fritos.

title: curried potatoes
directions: Parboil the potatoes until nearly done.
Cut them up and place in a casserole with the sour cream and soup.
Blend in the seasonings.
Top with the bread crumb and cheese mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add kidney beans.
In a large bowl, put hamburger and bean mixture.
Add tomatoes, lettuce, onions and cheese.
Top with Doritos and add salad dressing.
Toss until mixed evenly and serve.

title: sausage and mushrooms
directions: Soften pepper and onions in water in microwave.
Remove sausage from casing and roll into balls.
Place in water and fry. Put all other ingredients in crock-pot.
Add sauce.
Warm 4 hours. Can be done on top of stove also.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients.
Form into ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill.

title: dressing for potato salad
directions: Blend well and toss on cooked potatoes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin; make a white sauce with oleo, flour and milk.
Layer with potatoes, onion and white sauce.
Repeat.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and brown grated cheese or Cheez Whiz may be added to white sauce for cheese flavor.

title: tangerine pie
directions: Whip together and pour into 2 graham cracker crust pie shells. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Top with mandarin oranges (1 can for 2 pies).

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain, debone and flake salmon.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, onion powder, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke. Chill.
Shape salmon mixture.
Roll in nuts and parsley.
Chill. Yield:
12 servings.

title: butterscotch treat
directions: Combine flour, oats and brown sugar.
Cut in softened butter until it looks like crumbs.
Add nuts.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pat down.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
After cooling, break into crumbles.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add all others.
(Can use raisins if you wish, 1 cup.)
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.
Freezes well.

title: hawaiian baked pork chops
directions: Place pineapple in a large baking dish.
Place potato slices over the pineapple. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Season chops with salt and pepper and place on top of sweet potatoes. Arrange bacon strips over chops and cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tender.
Increase heat to 450°.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until browned.
Serves 6 people.

title: easy vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate or small casserole dish.
Cook broccoli to almost tender in a saucepan; drain.
Mix broccoli, onion, peppers, bacon and cheese in pie plate dish.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth in blender (15 seconds) or hand beat for 1 minute.
Pour other vegetables, cheese, etc. in pie plate.
Bake until golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated fresh fruit
directions: Marinate in Peach Schnapps overnight.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put drained pineapple into casserole. Add sugar and egg.
Mix cornstarch in water; pour over pineapple. Mix well.
Cut Parkay into inch slices; put on top.
Add cinnamon. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tri-colored summer pasta salad
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, cook carrots for 2 minutes. Add celery, both peppers and onion.
Cook for 4 more minutes.
Add broccoli, cook until water returns to boiling.
Remove from heat and drain.
Immediately cool with cold water.
Very important that the vegetables are completely cooled.
Set in the refrigerator. Cook pasta until al dente.
Drain and cool completely.
Toss pasta and vegetables together with dressing just before serving. Garnish with halved cherry tomatoes.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and 1/8 teaspoon each pepper, sage and thyme.
Shape firmly into 6 mini meat loaves.

title: german nut roll
directions: Use pastry blender.
Cut butter into flour and yeast until well mixed.
Mix water, eggs and sugar into dry ingredients.
Mix and let stand overnight in refrigerator in a large covered bowl. Divide into 4 parts.
Roll thin into a rectangle.
Combine remaining ingredients to make filling.
Divide filling into fourths.
Spreads over thin dough and roll.
Bake 2 rolls at a time at 350° on a cookie sheet until brown.
Slice.

title: corn chowder
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Stir in 1 cup skim milk gradually.
Heat slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in corn and salt.
Stir in remaining 1 cup skim milk gradually.
Heat to serving temperature; do not boil.
Stir in pepper.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mini chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 24 miniature muffin pan cups. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, whisk milk, butter, egg and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Spoon into prepared cups.
Bake 18 minutes or until just golden.
Unmold and cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix together in saucepan the sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk. Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and coconut.
Drop on waxed paper and let set until cool and firm.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: five layer dessert
directions: Mix flour and nuts together.
Cut in oleo as for pie crust until like fine crumbs.
Pat crumbs in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until delicately brown.
Cool.

title: mexican salad
directions: Shred lettuce and slice green onions into large salad bowl. Brown meat.
Add chopped onion and cook until tender.
Stir in beans, dressing, water and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: fan's favorite nuggets
directions: Prepare chicken nuggets according to package directions.
In small bowl, combine duck sauce and mustard.
Serve as dipping sauce for chicken nuggets.
Makes about 6 snack size servings.

title: red cinnamon pickle rings
directions: First day:
Peel, core and slice cucumbers into 1/2-inch rings.
Dissolve lime in enough water to cover rings.
Stir occasionally.
Cover with plate and weigh down.
Soak 24 hours in cool place.

title: mom's hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in square pan and add in layers each item listed. Pour milk over all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: banana pudding
directions: Stir 2 cups milk until thick; add 1 can Eagle Brand milk; mix well.
Add 1/2 of large Cool Whip (16 ounces) thawed; mix well and pour over a layer of bananas and vanilla wafers.
Add other 1/2 of Cool Whip on top.
You can add yellow food coloring to make pudding yellow, about 14 to 16 drops.
Make in a dish or pan size (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/8).
Makes about 12 servings.

title: grape cooler
directions: Pour over ice cubes.
This is easily increased to serve a crowd.

title: sticky cinnamon buns
directions: Mash
potato
and water through a colander.
Add enough warm water to make 2 cups.
Add	the
sugar
and
yeast;
let stand for 5 minutes.	Add the salt,
flour, lard or Crisco and beaten eggs; mix until smooth.
Add about
to
4 cups flour to make a medium stiff
dough.
Cover;
let
rise
until double in bulk. Prepare pans (9 x
x
2-inch oblong and a 9-inch
round cake pan); grease
generously
with
Crisco
and drizzle generously with dark Karo syrup in pan until bottom of pan is covered. Spread soft
butter over Karo.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Make 1 pie.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Then 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grilled beef steaks-bulgaria(govezhdy purzholy na skara)
directions: Grease both sides of steak with butter. Roast on grill for 5-6 minutes, or until browned. Lightly butter and salt both sides. Roast other side until brown.
Place on dish and sprinkle with salt and black pepper. Serves 4-6.

title: sausage gravy(to be served over biscuits; also known as sawmill gravy)
directions: Saute the sausage.
Sprinkle the flour over the sausage; stir. Gradually add the milk (more can be added if necessary).
Add the salt and pepper; cook until thickened.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: white chili
directions: Saute onions in oil till translucent.
Add garlic, chilies, cumin, oregano, and cayenne; cook 2 more minutes.
Add beans (with liquid) and broth; bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add chicken and cheese.
Stir till cheese melts.
(If cheese is not done just right, it will be stringy.)
Season with salt and pepper.
Ladle into bowls.
Garnish with a dollop of sour cream.

title: sausage gravy and biscuits
directions: Saute the sausage; crumble.
Drain all fat.
Make a white sauce of the butter or margarine, flour and milk.
Combine with sausage; heat together.
Add more milk for a thinner sauce.
Bake the prepared biscuit dough according to package.
Break biscuits open; put sausage gravy on top.
Serve with spiced peaches on side.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with Vanilla Sauce.

title: chocolate double fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8-inch pans.

title: easy berry cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Pour 1/2 of flour mixture in dish.
Add berries, then remaining flour mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: vegetable rice salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill.

title: sunshine soup
directions: Wash and dry zucchini. Cut off ends. Cut in 2-inch long, 1/2-inch wide strips. Saute the chopped onion in a little vegetable oil. When onion is soft, but not brown, add the zucchini and salt and pepper.
Cover with water and cook, uncovered, on medium heat until tender (do not overcook).

title: crab sandwiches
directions: Combine crab meat, shredded cheese, celery and parsley. Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, mustard and Tabasco sauce.
Toss crab meat mixture with dressing.
Split and toast muffins and spread with butter.
Spread crab meat mixture and 1 slice of cheese on each muffin.
Broil about 4 inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes, until cheese is melted and crab mixture is heated.
Cut in squares.

title: ham-cheese bagels
directions: Combine all chopped ingredients with olive oil and tomato sauce.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Put 2 teaspoons of mixture on a split mini bagel, then broil until bubbly.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place peeled and sliced apples in a 2-quart (8 x 8-inch) pan. Combine remaining ingredients, except butter, in a mixing bowl. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 325° until apples are tender.
Or cook in microwave for 12 to 16 minutes on High.

title: pumpernickel bread
directions: Combine all-purpose and rye flours.
Mix 2 cups flour mixture, salt, cereal, cornmeal and yeast in large bowl.
Combine water, molasses, chocolate and butter in saucepan; heat over low heat until butter and chocolate melt.
Gradually add to flour mixture; beat for 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally. Add potatoes and 1 cup flour mixture, or enough flour to make a thick batter.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in caraway seed and enough additional flour mixture to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board; cover dough with bowl and let rest 15 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 15 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning to grease all sides.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from drafts, until double in bulk.

title: zucchini-summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until just tender and drain.
Saute onions, pepper and tomatoes until tender.
Add soup, milk and sour cream together; add melted butter.
Butter 2-quart casserole dish.
Add in layers, starting with stuffing, vegetables and milk mixture. Cover with Mozzarella or Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Mix all other ingredients except cheese and crackers.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle generously cheese on top on crackers.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Cook cake mix in 2 layers.
When cool, split in 4 layers. Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture to use later.
Spread on top of each layer.
Mix the 1 1/2 cups of thawed whipped topping with the cup of mixture.
Ice top and sides of cake.
Put cake in airtight container for 3 days in refrigerator before serving.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In a large skillet, put in vegetable oil; add jumbo shrimp. Cook for 10 minutes on medium-high heat.
Add garlic, lemon juice and Italian spices; cook 2 minutes.
Add clam juice; cook for 3 minutes.
Add in precooked angel hair spaghetti; cook 15 minutes.

title: meat sauce and spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain off fat.
Mix with all ingredients.
Simmer until desired thickness, about one hour. Serve over spaghetti with hot rolls or Texas Toast, green salad or fruit.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni for 7 minutes or longer, drain.
In large skillet, brown beef and add onion, green pepper, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Cook 15 minutes approximately.
Drain; add macaroni and spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Place in buttered dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese melts.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook Jell-O pudding, sugar and milk until soft ball stage or exactly 1 minute after boiling starts.
Remove from burner, set pan into cold water in sink.
Stir butter in until thick, but thin enough to pour into buttered platter.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate truffle cookies
directions: In microwave or double boiler, melt unsweetened chocolate, 1 cup of chocolate chips and butter; cool 10 minutes.
In other bowl, beat sugar and eggs for 2 minutes.
Beat in vanilla and chocolate mixture.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt and beat into mixture.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Remove 1 cup dough and with lightly floured hands roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly puffed.
Cool 3 to 4 minutes and transfer to wire rack. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: cole slaw
directions: With a grater, grate cabbage, carrots and onion into a large bowl.
In a small bowl, mix mustard, mayonnaise, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
When it is well mixed, coat the grated vegetables until well mixed.
Chill and serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms, and pimentos in butter.
Mix mushroom soup, mayonnaise, onion mixture, noodles, and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350 degrees until bubbling.

title: scotch apple pie
directions: Slice apples in bottom of greased baking dish.
Cover with the brown sugar.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Add tomato paste, catsup and soup.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve on open-faced toasted buns.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Add cornstarch to sugar and mix well.
Add softened butter and egg yolk.
Cream well.
Add milk and blend; beat egg whites until frothy and add to mixture along with vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 375° until knife inserted in pie comes out clean.

title: thrifty steak
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in lightly greased shallow pan; put mixture into shape of a T-bone steak (1-inch thick).
Set oven control at broil and/or 550°.
Broil meat 3 to 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn, broil other side for 5 minutes.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add all ingredients to meat mixture. Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole #2
directions: Mix soup with liquid from the asparagus in a bowl to the consistency of gravy.
Discard remaining liquid from asparagus.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for 1 hour or until firm.

title: caramel treats
directions: Using the original Rice Krispies Treats recipe, add caramel topping to melted marshmallow mixture at step 1 just before adding cereal.
Follow remaining directions in steps 2 and 3. Put in freezer for 30 minutes and then cut in 2 x 2-inch squares.
Yields 24 treats.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Saute green pepper, celery and onion in butter in a large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling on bottom of a 7 x 14 x 2-inch cake pan.
Next, add crushed pineapple, including juice.
Add dry cake mix (spread evenly).
Slice butter over top and add chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be served with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: shaker pickles
directions: Put all ingredients in glass gallon jar and shake well each day for 7 days.
Keep in refrigerator after 7 days.
They are ready to eat.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach (do not cook).
In blender container combine spinach, Miracle Whip or real mayonnaise, parsley (kind bought in spice jar), pepper, onion and garlic powder.
Blend until fairly smooth consistency is reached.
Chill for 24 hours.
Serve.

title: trail bologna
directions: If there's any fat in meat, eliminate water.

title: punch
directions: Place ice in serving bowl.
Add first 4 ingredients.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and cherries.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a good boil.
In a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan or dish, line bottom of dish with whole graham crackers.
Pour cooked ingredients over crackers.
Put whole graham crackers on top.
Push lightly to set crackers in filling. Frost with thin layer of vanilla frosting.
Refrigerate. When crackers are soft, cut and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form into 2 large or 3 small balls with wet hands.
Roll in chopped walnuts and/or parsley flakes. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: surprise salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all the ingredients together.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Spread beans on a small platter.
Layer sour cream, then onions.
Sprinkle with chopped tomato, lettuce, cheese and salsa. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oysterettes
directions: Mix all together in a baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 250°. Stir often while baking.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Boil raisins, 2 cups water and shortening for about 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup water, sugar, soda, spices and flour.
Pour into well-greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix in order shown.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter lover's dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Serve with apple slices and banana chunks or any fruit chunks.

title: microwave frito pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Mix chili, tomato sauce and hamburger meat together.
In a casserole dish, layer Fritos, hamburger mixture, then Cheddar cheese; repeat.
Cover and microwave on High for 8 minutes.

title: kathy's krunch bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with unbroken crackers; top with pecans. Combine butter, oleo and vanilla in pan and cook on top of stove until sugar is dissolved.
Pour mixture over pecans and bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Take out of pan immediately and let cool.

title: glorified macaroni and cheese
directions: Saute onion and pimento in 1 tablespoon mayonnaise; do not brown.
Add the onion, remaining mayonnaise, pimento, soups and cheese to the macaroni.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: In a very large bowl, mix cottage cheese and dry Jell-O.
Mix well.
Add well drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip; add mandarin oranges last.
Refrigerate or chill in icebox.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: coconut pan cake
directions: Prepare cake by following directions on cake mix.
While cake is cooking, mix Eagle Brand cream and cream of coconut.
Take a wooden spoon, with a round handle, and punch holes in the cake. Pour cream mix, with a little coconut, over the cake.
Place in refrigerator and let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake; sprinkle with coconut.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add milk, then dry ingredients to eggs and beat.
Put bread and raisins in buttered baking dish.
Pour egg-milk mixture over bread and raisins.

title: "no peek" beef
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Don't take cover off while cooking. Serve over hot rice or noodles.

title: quick apple snack
directions: Spoon applesauce on toast; sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: easy caramel corn
directions: Microcook marshmallows, margarine and brown sugar for 3 minutes on High (stir twice).
Add soda, stir and cook 30 seconds more.
Stir in popped corn and cool on waxed paper.

title: peabody hot crab dip
directions: Saute white and green onion, garlic and celery in butter. In large mixing bowl, combine sauted mixture with cream cheese. Mix well. Add 1 tablespoon Old Bay seasoning, 1 teaspoon salt and 2 teaspoons black pepper. Add chopped artichokes with 1/2 cup of the marinade from the artichokes jar. Mix well. Fold in mayonnaise and 4 shakes of Tabasco. Gently fold in cream and crab meat. Be careful not to break lumps. Place in chafing dish.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: quick custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients, except coconut, into blender in the order given.
Blend about 1 minute.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie tin. Coconut may be sprinkled on top, if desired. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma's best sugar cookies
directions: Let oleo soften; add sugar, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Add oil and egg. Add flour gradually. Add vanilla and nuts last. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until medium brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix dry jello with other ingredients and chill.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer dish in order of ingredients.
Layer bottom with lettuce, a layer of tomatoes, layer of mayonnaise, etc.
Top with bacon bits.

title: nutty crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Line foil with divided Waverly crackers.
Sprinkle pecans on top of crackers.
In boiler, boil for 3 minutes the butter, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over crackers and bake for 10 minutes. Turn off oven and let crackers set for 30 seconds.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: potato patties
directions: Mix shredded potatoes with egg, onion, flour and salt.
Drop from a tablespoon into hot fat in a frypan.
Fry on both sides until crisp.

title: hot apple pineapple
directions: Mix pineapple and apple pie filling.
Put into greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and bread crumbs. Spread on top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: banana pudding
directions: Crumble enough cookies to cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish to 1 inch thickness.
Set aside.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Cut candy bars in small pieces.
Mix milk with pudding and beat.
Add to bars and Cool Whip.
Combine diced apples with other ingredients.

title: canned salsa
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes; bring to a simmer 10 minutes.
Add cut up vegetables, spices and vinegar.
Cook over low heat until desired thickness.
Put in sterile jars; place jars in hot bath and boil for 20 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, Crisco and butter. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour and soda.
Mix. By hand, stir in oats, pecans, coconut, orange slices and corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Makes a bunch.

title: heath toffee bar coffee cake
directions: Melt
margarine in a brownie pan while oven preheats to 350°. Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, vanilla, margarine and nuts. Mix just until blended.

title: lindburg relish
directions: Put all vegetables through a food chopper and add all of the salt.
Let it set for 2 hours and then place it in a colander and drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Let stand until sugar dissolves (do not heat).
Put both mixes together and mix well. Place in freezer containers and enjoy later.

title: california club salad
directions: Into a large bowl, combine first 8 ingredients.
Toss lightly to mix.
Garnish with egg slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wolf chili pie
directions: Layer 1 1/2 cups corn chips, onion, 3/4 cup cheese and chili in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with remaining corn chips. Bake in preheated oven at 375° about 25
minutes. Top with remaining cheese and continue baking 5 more minutes. Garnish with sour cream and ripe olives, if desired.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish with bacon.
Pour in rice. Wrap deboned chicken breasts in bacon and place on top of rice. Pour soup, milk and sherry mixture over.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350°, covered with foil, for 45 minutes, then 45 minutes uncovered.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease a glass casserole dish and put a layer of potatoes, layer of onions and layer of asparagus.
Dot with butter; repeat each layer until all is used.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°, covered.
Uncover and lay cheese on top.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted and browned, approximately 10 minutes more.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs, flour, bananas, nuts, vanilla and soda.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions.
Drain Ro-Tel and combine in skillet.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook liquid down.
Cut cheese into small pieces and add to tomatoes.
Add chopped chicken.
Fill tortillas with mix.
Roll up and place in baking pan.
Pour remaining mix that's leftover them and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: chutney eggs
directions: Cut eggs in 1/2; remove yolks.
Mash yolks.
Add bacon, chutney and mayonnaise.
With pastry tube, fill white with yolk mixture.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Prepare white cake mix and add Oreo cookies to batter before baking.
Save some of the cookies to garnish the top of your cake.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes.
When cake is cool, top with icing of your choice.
You may either use 9 x 13-inch pan or round 9-inch pan or bake into cupcakes.

title: three c. bread
directions: Combine
eggs,	oil
and
milk.
In
a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add egg mixture.
Mix only enough to thoroughly combine. Stir in carrots, coconut, cherries, raisins and pecans.
Pour into 2 greased
and
floured
loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1
hour.
Test with toothpick.
If loaf gets too brown, loosely cover with foil as it bakes.

title: california spaghetti salad
directions: Chop all vegetables very small.
Cook spaghetti and let cool. Toss all ingredients into spaghetti.
Refrigerate for 8 hours before serving.
Serve cold.
This is a really good salad!

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix sugar, egg, vinegar and flour.
Cook until thick.
Let set overnight or until cool.
Mix marshmallows, peanuts, apples and Cool Whip.
Add thickened mixture and apple mixture together. Chill.

title: fancy coleslaw
directions: Toss cabbage and celery together.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with cabbage and celery.

title: herb and fruit vinegars
directions: Crush the tarragon leaves slightly to release the aroma. Combine with the vinegar and garlic and pour into a jar.
Cover.

title: dairy potato bake
directions: In large bowl, stir together the potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with corn flake crumbs. Drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until set.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add hominy and chilies.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish and grate 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese on top of casserole.
Bake approximately 15 minutes in a 350° oven or until cheese is melted.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and drain.
Heat soup and margarine over low heat.
Blend in sour cream.

title: dried beef-macaroni casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup and milk well.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Prepare at least 4 hours ahead of cooking or let set overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix beans, corn, celery, green pepper and onion.
Alternate a layer of vegetables with a layer of soup, grated cheese and then sour cream.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Melt margarine and stir in crackers and almonds.
Spread on top of casserole and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Divide in 1/2; make 2 long rolls. Wrap in foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
Unwrap and place on broiler pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Turn over in 45 minutes. Cool.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: lemon cream delight
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crushed cookies.
Line bottom and sides of an 8 x 8-inch pan with mixture.
Mix Dream Whip according to instructions.
Add softened cream cheese and powdered sugar. Cook lemon pie filling and let cool.

title: cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in milk and cook over medium-low heat until slightly thickened.
Combine a little of the hot mixture with beaten egg yolk.
Return to hot mixture and cook until thickened.
Stir in vanilla and butter. Pour into baked pastry shell.
Top cooled filling with meringue made by beating egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar.
Brown in oven at 425°.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix together and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and cool in pan for 5 minutes. Take off of cookie sheet and place on slightly damp dishtowel. Cool.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in hot water until done.
Mash with potato masher.
Pick out strings if in potatoes.
Add butter while potatoes are still hot.
Add sugars, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add eggs and beat well.
Use about 1/2 cup milk to thin mixture.
Pour into prepared 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Turn heat down to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.
When pie is done, dust with powdered sugar.

title: scallops harborside style
directions: If using large-sized sea scallops, slice horizontally through the center.
Place scallops in an oven pan containing a little butter and sherry.
Sprinkle with topping made of crumbs, garlic salt and paprika.
Dot with butter and broil until done, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and baking soda in a mixing bowl. Stir in buttermilk and beat until batter is smooth.
Stir in salt and onion.
Drop heaping tablespoonful of batter into a deep fryer or a pan of hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: mom's zucchini soup
directions: Fry and drain sausage, add celery and cook 10 minutes.
Add cut up zucchini, onion and tomatoes and spices and cook 20 minutes.
Add 2 chopped green peppers and cook 10 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread and Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin squares(low-fat)
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on apple juice in 1-quart saucepan to soften. Add water.
Heat over low heat until gelatin is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix pumpkin, brown sugar, cinnamon, ginger and cloves in medium bowl; stir in gelatin mixture until smooth.
Refrigerate until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon, stirring occasionally.

title: brownie delight
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa powder, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, oil and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa powder, gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups boiling water. Pour liquid mixture evenly over batter in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve warm or chilled in individually dessert dishes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in thin strips; brown in oil.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and cup of water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Add green peppers and cook 10 minutes.
Blend together cornstarch and 3 tablespoons of water; stir in meat mixture.
Serve over rice or with mashed potatoes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cook meat overnight in crock-pot or else just quickly fry meat if not enough time. Stir last 3 ingredients together and either put in crock-pot for a few hours or in skillet, if frying. Heat and simmer for a few minutes in pan.

title: egg salad
directions: Boil eggs and grate. Add sweet relish, salad dressing, pimentos, salt and sugar. Mix well. (Do not get too thin.)

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool and add vanilla and liqueur.

title: mashed potato and creamed cheese casserole
directions: Put potatoes in large bowl.
Add cream cheese, onion, eggs and flour.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Increase speed to high and beat well until light and fluffy.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Cover with onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 300° oven for 35 minutes.
If dish is prepared ahead, do not add onion rings until ready to bake.

title: who dat?
directions: Brown the Cajun sausage and ground beef with pepper and onions. Drain all grease off. In large Dutch oven, add tomatoes, tomato sauce, beans, sliced sausages, salt and pepper. Cook 2 hours. Serve with rice.

title: easy beef tortilla pizzas
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in large skillet over medium high heat until beef loses pink color.
Pour off drippings. Sprinkle oregano and salt over beef, stirring to combine.
Place tortillas on 2 large baking sheets.
Lightly brush surface of each tortilla with oil.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 3 minutes. Divide beef mixture evenly over tops of tortillas.
Divide tomato and desired topping over beef mixture.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Layer in order and sprinkle a few shrimp on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine
first	3
ingredients;
mix well.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Add flour, cinnamon, cloves, soda and salt.
Add applesauce; mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown 1 1/2 pounds of ground meat and season with garlic salt, oregano and basil to taste.
May add mushrooms if desired.
Bake in oven at 325° for approximately 3 hours.
May need to add water as it cooks.
Also may be cooked in crock-pot all day on low. This sauce is also good with lasagna and pizza.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Put water into 4 gallon or 5 gallon boiling pot.
Add all ingredients.
Wait until veggies are tender, then add Kitchen Bouquet for color.
Then add seafood, chicken and whatever else appeals to you, baby shrimp, 5 pounds and crab claws, 2 pounds.

title: no peek stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients together in a Dutch oven; cover.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together, except the herbal season dressing.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle the dressing on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.
Serve hot.

title: italian chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together water, rice, tomatoes, cheese spread, onions and 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and remaining Italian seasoning.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
